host_about: I was born in Athens, Greece in 1968. I studied French Literature in the National and Kapodistrian University of Athens and History of Art in Sorbonne University. I speak Greek, English, French, Italian and Spanish. I like traveling a lot, I have been in a lot of places... England, Italy, France, Spain, Portugal, Holland, Romania, Bulgaria, Turkey, Morocco, Tunisia, Thailand, Phuket, Indonesia, Bali, Kenya, Dubai, Bahrain... I have worked as interpreter and translator, conferences organizer, personal assistant to Managing Directors and my last job was as chief editor in Economist Intelligent Life magazine for Greece. In 2013 I founded with my husband a Trading Company of Greek Standardized Food Products, wishing to promote our unique products all over the world. I am also the cultural editor in (URL HIDDEN) an on-line photographic magazine. I like swimming, exercising, hearing music, reading, painting, watching movies, traveling, being with my friends. My house is full of paintings and souvenirs from my trips all over the world. I love my beautiful husband, Thanos, my family, my niece, my friends, the interesting company of new acquaintances. I believe in 'carpe diem', which means 'seize the day', a life motto which I have painted in my body. We have no children and we live a beautiful life with our friends.

In the last century, it has become one of the most charming residential quarter of the capital, with many historical places and elegant buildings, Liberty style villas, boutiques, shops, restaurants, patisseries, coffee shops and cool night clubs where spending a pleasant and exciting time. name: Cosy apartment in Vienna
summary: Hello fellow travellers! I'm renting my two room apartment
description: Hello fellow travellers! I'm renting my two room apartment
host_about:
I love reading books (mostly novels or essays on psychology and translation theory), dancing and travelling of course! I only visited a few europen countries and the USA, so I still I have lot to see and visit! I'd love to go in India and Sri Lanka, maybe taking a bigger tour and passing from Pakistan as well. But I'd also like to go to Marokko or Tunisia... let's say I'd like to go everywhere around the world! I still do not have a plan but it's on my list :)
I'm a traveller, but not a turist, I like to meet the local people, talk to them and try to do a full immersion in the new culture. I do not travel just for seeing new places, I like to travel to experience a new way of living and thinking. That's why I think that airbnb is perfect for my purpose :) My place is not a elengant hotel, it's a cozy 2room apartment and you will feel like at home. So if you are looking for a super new cool apartment, that's not the right place. But if you are looking for clean and cozy place and a friendly italian host, here I am! :)

Je suis née à Lyon, venue à Paris à 18 ans faire mes études d'arts dramatiques en faisant un tour par la restauration j'ai finalement terminé responsable du restau! Petit détour par Los Angeles ou j'ai habité durant deux ans. Voilà maintenant je sais à peu près parler anglais correctement, il était temps! De retour sur Paris, je retrouve mes livres, mon ciné spécial rediffusion Fellini, les petits café, la vie parisienne, j'adore! I recycle so please make sure you throw plastic, cans and glasses in the proper plastic bag provided (just one bin for any recycling material) and then when you check out leave it by the black bins outside the building.  Rubbish must be put inside the big bl
host_about:
Hello, I'm a friendly Italian man with a very positive outlook on life. 
I am an endlessly curious. I love to experience the world with eyes wide open. I never stop exploring, discovering and evolving.
I love the Arts and creative people! Life to me is a storybook full of fascinating tales. I amass information 'on the hoof' and very little passes me by. Understanding what makes others tick is meat and drink to me and proves to be a source of endless joy.
I always keep my mind active. I love beauty in all forms, I am well educated and I like to remain totally classless. This makes it easy for me to get on with just about any sort of person. I am thought-provoking and even quite deep on occasions.
I organise luxury tours in Italy for small parties and occasionally I escort them, as I am a professional tour guide too. I get involved in other exciting things which keep me busy too, such as painting, reading books, newspaper and cultural magazines, photography, video editing, cycling, theatre, music, fitness and movies.
I strongly believe a very clean, secure, welcoming feel, and comfortable house is of paramount importance for travellers who don't want to break their bank account! 
I have been travelling on my own since the age of 14! I have been an exchange student in Baltimore for a year at the age of 18  and then at 20 I visited 36 States in the U.S. on a three cross Country tour. Been in Hawaii, Canada, Singapore and Malaysia, Maldives, Brazil,  Mexico, Costa Rica, Morocco, Tunisia, Cape Verde, Turkey and all Western European Countries.
When you stay at my place I will make you feel a member of my family as my life's golden rule is to treat others as you wish to be treated! 
I am always on an adventure. Enjoy hearing about people's travels and life styles. It stands to good reason why you would enjoy staying in my home: it is a warm and caring place. 
I look forward to meeting you and show the true Mediterranean hospitality with an English twist!
Sincerely,
Adriano :-)

Socializzo con facilità, rido di gusto, mi intrigano i cervelli acuti e mi innervosicono gli arroganti prepotenti; mi annoiano i "lagnosi" fine a se stessi ma ascolto volentieri chi ha bisogno di un consiglio o di un sostegno per trovare una soluzione. Non sopporto le ingiustizie, la superficialità e mi innamoro di chi è capace di godere delle piccole cose e di chi, come dice Aristotele, "prova un senso di dubbio e di meraviglia, riconosce di non sapere e per liberarsi dall'ignoranza ricerca il conoscere..."

name: Nice & Cozy Apartment Downtown MTL
summary: Perfect apartment for a short trip or a longer stay. Located at the heart, downtown Montreal. All included and five minute walk downhill to the nicest restaurants, bars malls and metro. For hockey fans, the Habs are playing three blocks away! :)
space: In the room you will find a comfortable queen-size bed with all bedding, a small worktable and a wardrobe. There is a bath-shower in the bathroom. In the living room, there are one 3 seater-sofa and and a double sofa bed where two additional guest can sleep. There is also a TV equipped with a HDMI cable and a DVD.
description: Perfect apartment for a short trip or a longer stay. Located at the heart, downtown Montreal. All included and five minute walk downhill to the nicest restaurants, bars malls and metro. For hockey fans, the Habs are playing three blocks away! :) In the room you will find a comfortable queen-size bed with all bedding, a small worktable and a wardrobe. There is a bath-shower in the bathroom. In the living room, there are one 3 seater-sofa and and a double sofa bed where two additional guest can sleep. There is also a TV equipped with a HDMI cable and a DVD. The kitchen is well-equipped in order to allow you to prepare some good homemade meals during your stay. The equipment includes a gas stove and oven, a fridge and freezer, a microwave oven, a toaster, an electric kettle, a coffeemaker, pots and kitchen utensils.  In addition to certain basic groceries, you will also find anything you need to breakfast before going to discover Montreal. There are coin-op washers and dryers on the top -
neighborhood_overview: Located at the heart of downtown Montreal, but on a quiet street, and next door to McGill University, the apartment is at a perfectly emplacement. You will be at a 5 minute walk from the famous Ste-Catherine street and all its shops, malls, coffee, restaurants and bars.  You will also be at a 10 minute walk from the Bell Center where you can see great shows and also the hockey games of the best team in the world :) The Mount Royal Park is at about 15 minute walk and the Old Port and Old Montreal are at about 20 minute walk. Less than 10 minutes away, you will find groceries and drugstores. There is also a supermarket and a 24h drugstore at about 7 minute walk. The Quartier des Spectacles, which hosts several festivals during summer time, including the Francofolies, the Festival international de Jazz and the Just for Laughs Festival, is at about 15 minute walk.
transit: The apartment is located at a five-minute walk from Peel Station and at walking distance (from 2 to 10 minutes) to several bus stops ((PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN)). There is a BIXI station located on Maisonneuve Street between Stanley and Peel (4 minute walk). There is also a taxi station just down the street at the corner of Stanley and Sherbrooke. (2 minute walk). ARRIVAL From airport You can take a cab that will cost you a fixed rate of 40. You can also take the 747, for which the fare is 10 for unlimited travel throughout STM bus and métro networks during 24 consecutive hours. Once in the shuttle, you can get off at Lionel-Groulx metro station, take the metro until Peel station and then walk 5 minutes to be home. You can also get off at the intersections of Peel and René-Lévesque and then walk 10 minutes to be home.  From train station You can either walk (20 minutes), take the bus 107 at the corner of Peel and De La Gauchtière and stop at the corner of Peel and Sherbrooke (13 minutes,
host_about:
I work for a law firm in Montreal. As a host, it will be quite easy to make myself available at any time since my office is located 10 minutes away from the apartment.

I like to travel, play sports and do activities with friends.  My favorite trips were in Scotland, Tunisia, Spain, France and Washington D.C. Next on my list are Australia, Italy, Macedonia, Portugal, Croatia and Greece.

I will be more than happy to welcome you at my apartment and give you advices on what to visit in Montreal, from the best restaurants, shops and attractions. I hope you will enjoy your stay!

Neighborhood grocery store is just a couple of blocks away. It's home to many Kosher and non-Kosher dining opportunities, including steak houses, sushi, Japanese, French-Japanese, Chinese, Thai, Mexican, Tunisian, Persian, Italian, Vietnamese Pho, Pan-Asian, Indian, Mediterranean, Middle Eastern, delicatessan,  gourmet sausages and hamburgers, pizza, bakeries, French bakeries, Starbucks, Coffee Bean & Tea Leaf, Baskin Robbins 31 Flavors ice cream, frozen yogurt, and candy stores, all within a short walk. We are just a short walk or drive to Beverly Hills, and world-famous Rodeo Drive, and a short drive to internationally known trendy North Robertson high-end luxury boutique row.
notes: Your TV is internet ready, with Netflix, YouTube, and other internet channels.  Please note that the kitchen is not available for cooking or preparing meals. You can share our coffee and tea, and use the microwave to heat water. We will provide cups and utensils. Do not bring any food from outside of the house, please, and no food or drinks other than plain water in your room, please. (updated 1-31-17)
transit: Public transit is good, with easy bus service to the beach, West Hollywood and much of West Los Angeles. A short bus ride to light rail transit that connects to Downtown LA, the beach, and much more of LA County. Half hour ride to airport, LAX. interaction: We are here to welcome you, and for when you need us. If you like privacy, this bedroom with ensuite bath and its own entrance is perfect. You are just steps away from the kitchen and yard. Viviane is a native French speaker.
house_rules: -Our house rules are here to help everyone have an enjoyable experience in our home. We want you to have a clean and tidy place to enjoy and relax - Please remove shoes and sandals in your bedroom and our house. host_about:
I love Paris and quite particularly my district where life is enjoyable. Sportswoman, I am a member of a club of swimming and move by bicycle.

I am quite particularly interested in the ecology and in the well-being. 

The cooking is a part of my everyday life and I like sharing with my friends my new recipes, the new products which I discover on markets or in the organic cooperatives.

The culture generally (cinema, music, exhibitions, gastronomy) are a part of my life.

I lived in London, Madrid, in New Jersey, in Morocco and I travelled in Germany, Italy, Spain, Israel, Bulgaria, Italy, Tunisia, in the Caribbean, in Guinea-Conakry, in the United States... These last years, my Thaï friends shared with me their everyday life of the authentic Thailand of the South.

My life motto : "think outside the box and stay the course" !


J'aime Paris et tout particulièrement mon quartier où il fait bon vivre. Sportive, je suis membre d'un club de natation et me déplace à vélo.

Je m'intéresse tout particulièrement à l'écologie et au bien-être. 

La cuisine fait partie de mon quotidien et j'aime partager avec mes amis mes nouvelles recettes, les nouveaux produits que je découvre sur les marchés ou dans les coopératives bio.

La culture en général (cinéma, musique, expos, gastronomie...) font partie de ma vie.

La couture, le bricolage, la fabrication de produits cosmétiques naturels sont mes hobbies.

J'ai vécu à Londres, Madrid, dans le New Jersey, au Maroc et j'ai voyagé en Allemagne, Italie, Espagne, Israël, Bulgarie, Italie, Tunisie, dans les Caraïbes, en Guinée-Conakry, aux Etats Unis...  Ces dernières années, mes amis Thaï m'ont fait partager leur vie quotidienne de l'authentique Thaïlande du sud.

Ma devise : sortir des sentiers battus et garder le cap !

neighborhood_overview: Portobello Market in West London is one of the most famous street markets in the world. It is a popular destination for Londoners and tourists alike. Portobello Road goes straight through the heart of Notting Hill, the trendy area of London made famous by the film. Indeed, so famous is the film Notting Hill that I find scarcely a week goes by without someone or other asking me about the various set locations: the blue door, the travel bookshop, the garden fence and so on. Portobello Market takes up most of what is actually more properly called Portobello Road, it stretches for around two miles, although on a crowded saturday afternoon it takes quite a while to walk from end to end.
transit: Getting to Notting Hill by Bus There are also many buses operating across the whole of Notting Hill, including routes (phone number hidden) and 452 amongst others – take a look at Transport for London’s Kensington & Chelsea Bus Route maps for more details. You’ll find that buses operate right through Notting Hill, with many servicing some of the area’s main larger roads such as Notting Hill Gate, Westbourne Grove, Kensington Park Road, Pembridge Villas, Ladbroke Road, Westbourne Park Road and more. You can easily reach Notting Hill by bus if you’re travelling from Chelsea, Kensington, South Kensington, Knightsbridge, Shepherd’s Bush and Paddington. There are also a number of buses from further afield…but as the journey time can be considerable (taking into account the London traffic), we’d advise taking the Underground instead!

neighborhood_overview: Theatres and halls, triangles and strip malls, rowdy bars and shopping centers—Shepherd’s Bush is a mumbling west London neighbourhood that doesn’t disappoint. The neighborhood’s 8-acre triangular green space teems with activity and invites pleasure-strollers and passers-by to peruse the cafes, pubs, and theatres along the park’s surrounding streets. When local labels aren’t enough, check out Shepherd Bush’s claim to fame—the neighbourhood is home to Europe’s largest urban shopping complex. One of the most diverse and eclectic neighbourhoods of London. Great restaurants; Syrian, Ethiopian, Caribbean and the best falafels in the world just 5 minutes walk away in buzzing Shepherds Bush market. Indulge your stomach, then your wallet at Westfield shopping centre which is 5 minutes away. And then take a stroll down to Notting Hill and Portobello Road, with a stop off in Holland Park on your way home. Perfect!
transit: 5 minutes walk to Shepherds Bush Market tube station, 10 minutes walk to Shepherds Bush tube station, two minutes walk to bus stops on Uxbridge Road. There are plenty of bus routes in the area that will take you all over London. There are also Santander Bike Stations surrounding the property if you feel like a cycle around the city. Check out the TFL Santander Cycles website for locations and information.

neighborhood_overview: What's not to love about the neighbourhood?! Askew Road is two minute's walk away and offers fabulous bakeries and cake shops, an excellent butcher, two supermarkets, a library and a great pub. You also have the option of dining out at Tunisian, Persian, Japanese, Thai, Nepalese and good old fish and chips. All on the Askew Road!  No need to get on a bus or tube if you want evening entertainment. Apart from pubs and restaurants, we are less than a mile from the newly-refurbished Bush Theatre, Bush Hall (boasting a famous history of now legendary acts), as well as the Shepherds Bush Empire for more music events.  We are also less than a mile from Westfield Shopping Centre; countless shops and a multiplex cinema at your disposal. For the more outdoorsy, it's a 20 min walk to the river through Ravenscourt Park (three playgrounds, basketball courts, football and tennis, cafe and paddling pool), and once on the river you can walk, bike or jog for miles in either direction.
notes: This property can only be rented for a minimum of a week's stay.
transit: Transport couldn't be easier. Buses a five min walk away will whisk you into Notting Hill and the West End within 30 mins, while the four tube lines (Central, Piccadilly, Circle and Hammersmith and City) take you directly to virtually any destination in London.

neighborhood_overview: My neighborhood is quiet, with a mix of recent and century-old houses (like mine) and tall trees, and just a couple of blocks from the North East shore looking onto the NYC harbor.  From there you can see Brooklyn, Manhattan and NJ, as well as the Verrazano bridge all the boat traffic in the harbor. At walking distance you will find supermarkets, delis, laundromats, pharmacy, a Chinese take-out, a burger place and more.
notes: You are welcome to bring your dog as long as he is not aggressive. I have a very sweet dog, Kosmo, who will love it if you throw the ball for him!! Cats would be a problem as my dog chases them.
transit: Traveling from/to Manhattan is very easy: the Staten Island ferry (at Battery Park in Manhattan) is free, runs 24 hours, and leaves every half hour (every 15 minutes at peak hours). At the ferry terminal in Staten Island you catch the subway and get off at the 3rd stop (Clifton) and we are just a block away from the subway station. So 30 minutes for the ferry ride and another 15 minutes for the Staten Island metro, in 45 minutes you are in lower Manhattan. And that is just the cost of pubic transportation, 2.75 (or less with a weekly unlimited card). There are also express buses running from various points of Manhattan to Staten Island. With these express buses you can travel to/from Manhattan in 20-30 minutes. The cost of these is 6. From Brooklyn you can take the R to the last station, 86th Street, and catch the S79 bus going across the Verrazano bridge. We are at equal distance between the ferry terminal and the Verrazano bridge. The closest airport is Newark, 20 min.  and about
access: Check in is from 2 PM until as late as you'd like (you don't have to see me to get in) and check out is by 11 AM. But as long as I don't have guests on the day of your arrival or departure, I am very flexible, please just ask. You will have access to our immense backyard and large front yard too (the entire land is 19,000 sq ft!), terrace with the big table, lots of chairs and, the hammock under the tall tall trees, our 14-ft trampoline. There is an area with a table, chairs and a gas grill that's just for you, but you are welcome to use any part of the garden .
interaction: Once you confirm your reservation you will get my email and phone number and can call me any time. I live upstairs form the apartment and I am available for any questions but the space is completely separate and has total privacy.
house_rules: No smoking inside please. If you smoke in the garden please pick up your cigarette butts.

Hello,

Voici quelques éléments utiles à savoir sur ma personnalité

Bienveillance, intégrité, générosité, confiance,créativité et curiosité sont les qualités que mes amis bien aimés me prêtent.

Ce dont je ne peux pas me passer:respirer, lire, écrire, apprendre, partager, danser.

Mes habitudes de voyage "Comme chez Soi": France,Espagne,Maroc.

Mes "coups de cœur": Lisbonne, Porto, Sintra (Portugal), Rome (Italie), Chef Chaouen (Maroc)

host_about:
In the heart of Ealing, known as Queen of suburbs, The Caspian offers cosy rooms with continental breakfast in a friendly family environment. We have been serving the local and international community for decades and the hospitality of The Caspian has not diminished over these years.


Caspian is conveniently nestled on the corner of Haven Green. Set in a Victorian Era house, all rooms are double glazed with TV, free WIFI and seating area provided. Some rooms have period features and large windows with garden view.

We offer a large variety of rooms: diversified by their size, colour and price.

We have onsite parking and a meeting room is available for hire. It offers a pleasant ambiance for board meetings or private reunions.





The Caspian is a 2 minutes’ walk from Ealing Broadway Station and 15 minutes from Central London. Ealing Broadway shopping centres, restaurants and all amenities are a short walk. Our sister La Baguette coffee shop/restaurant offers delicious Tunisian and international food (10% discount for Hotel guests). 

So much is going on in Ealing: Ealing Summer Festivals (Jazz, Blues, Comedy, Beer, Carnival) in July, Ealing Half Marathon in September.
 ...and around Ealing: Sport and Music events at Wembley Stadium all year, and the unique grand Westfield Shopping Malls is a short bus or train ride. The significant Walpole Park along with Pitzhanger Manor are a short stroll from Caspian.

Caspian Hotel is just 20 minutes’ drive from Heathrow Airport. The M4, M40 and A406 motorways are only 5 minutes’ drive.





The Caspian has been visited by top consultant Alex Polizzi from The Hotel Inspector TV Series on 3 consecutive years.

neighborhood_overview: Le quartier est très agréable, calme, vert, aéré. Il se trouve à proximité de la vie parisienne (cafés, restaurants,...) mais loin des désagréments et du bruits. De nombreux commerces, des marchés, boulangeries,... sont très proches, où vous trouverez des produits typiques et de qualité.
notes: Les horaires d'arrivée sont compris entre 17h et 20h, les horaires de départ entre 7h30 et 11h. En cas de départ et d'arrivée en dehors de ces créneaux, merci de m'en parler avant d'effectuer votre réservation, je pourrai vous facturer un forfait supplémentaire. Merci de m'informer personnellement et à l'avance de vos horaires d'arrivée et de départ pour pouvoir m'organiser. Afin d'éviter de mauvaises surprises, merci de laisser l'appartement en bon état de propreté et d'effectuer un ménage régulier. Pour les locations de longue durée, au delà d'une semaine, un service de ménage d'1 heure une fois par semaine inclus dans la location sera obligatoire. Une place de parking est possible dans l'immeuble, me consulter pour le tarif.
transit: La station de métro est « Nation », ligens 1, 2, 6 ou 9 et RER A. Si vous arrivez avec le RER A ou la ligne 9, prendre la sortie "boulevard Voltaire", tourner à gauche en sortant sur la place de la Nation jusqu’à la rue Jaucourt. Prendre la rue Jaucourt jusqu'à la rue du Sergent Bauchat. Si vous arrivez avec les lignes de métro 1 – 2 ou 6 prendre  la sortie "avenue Dorian" et suivre la rue Jaucourt en face de vous en sortant jusqu'à la rue du Sergent Bauchat.
access: Accès à l'appartement entier : Salon + chambre + cuisine + salle de bain/toilettes + balcon
interaction: Je suis disponible par e-mails pour pour répondre à vos questions et échanger avant votre arrivée. Si je ne suis pas à Paris, c'est Karine qui vous accueillera, vous montrera l’appartement, vous donnera tous les renseignements dont vous avez besoin et réceptionnera l'appartement à votre départ.
house_rules: Il s'agit d'un appartement privé, merci d'entre prendre soin. Afin d'éviter de mauvaises surprises, merci de laisser l'appartement en bon état de propreté et d'effectuer un ménage régulier. Respecter l'environnement très calme de l'appartement et de l'immeuble. Merci de ne pas faire de bruit après 22h et le dimanche matin. Respecter le bois (parquet du salon et de la chambre et plan de travail de la cuisine). Si vous déplacez des meubles, objets et ustensiles, merci de les replacer à leur emplacement initial avant de quitter l'appartement. Parisienne depuis 20 ans, j'ai vécu longtemps à l’étranger pour des raisons professionnelles. Je travaille actuellement à Tunis mais suis souvent de retour à Paris.
J'aime beaucoup mon quartier à Paris, vivant mais calme, proche de tout, de la Seine, des jardins, des cafés et restaurants, ds marchés avec beaucoup de commerces. Sur le balcon, on peut voir la Tour Eiffel et le Sacré Cœur mais aussi beaucoup d'oiseaux qui passent et même des mouettes !

space: I worked for the City of Paris for several years and love the city, its unique secrets and romantic places. My bookshelves are full of little stories - and art : I collect works (paintings, drawings, photography, sculptures).

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is lively (fruit + veggie market every tuesday and friday along the boulevard), with its many Chinese cantinas and supermarkets, its Tunisian restaurants, its art galleries, noisy cafes where you can see concerts until 2 AM and clubs where you would dance till dawn. But the appartment is a very quiet nest :) MY FAVOURITES… in the neighborhood  -pastry : Thierry Meunier, 15 rue de Belleville -café for the morning  : Café Chéri(e), 44 bd de la Villette or Folies, 8 rue de Belleville -café for the afternoon : Le Floréal, 73 rue du Faubourg du Temple, or L’Autre Café, 62 rue Jean-Pierre Timbaud, or Le Soleil, 136 boulevard de Ménilmontant -café for the evening : Le Carillon, 18 rue Alibert, or My Woodie, 103 rue Oberkampf or Le Saint Sauveur, 11 rue des Panoyaux, or UDO, 4 rue Neuve Popincourt, or Le Perchoir, 14 rue Crespin du Gast -free concert venue : L’International, 5/7 rue Moret -concert venue : Le Nouveau Casino, 109 rue Oberkampf -Club : La Java, 105 rue du Faubour
notes: I happen to have a cat - usually, I take it with me when I leave the apartment, but can offer a discount price if you agree to keep it with you (she's lovely!) Just common sense politeness : if you happen to break something (which can happen), just tell me!
transit: From Charles de Gaulle Airport, there is a Paris by train connecting to the Gare du Nord : from there, either the bus 46 or the metro line 2 will lead you to my place.  From my place, with metro 11, it takes approx. 5mn to get to Centre Pompidou, 7mn to Parc des uttes Chaumont or, in the other direction, to Hotel de Ville (and Notre Dame de Paris), and 12mn to the Louvre. A night bus stops at 200m.

name: Living Art Apartment near St.Peter square
summary: The house's name can be read in two ways: Living heart, or the Art of Living. These two interpretations encompass the meaning of this house. A house made with heart, over ten years ago, because the architect who designed it also lives in it. The project was inspired by the city it's located in, Rome- Vatican City. So as the 'Eternal' city will fill your eyes with art and history, this apartment, just ten minutes from St Peter's Square, encompasses the history and art of Living.
space: Enjoying the space will have you feeling you're in more than one culture at the same time: in Rome of course, but also in Andalucia- which inspired the garden, in the Mahgreb, thanks to the beautiful tiles made by a Tunisian artisan, as well as in Brazil, where many of the apartment's artefacts are from.

Ciao! My name is Gianni and after 25 years of living in Roma now I live in Milan.
I am a journalist and television deal even if i would love to be a chef !!!
I have a "wonderful" dog named Giasone.
I was born and lived by the sea for 20 years so now, when i i have the chance i escape from the city prefering the peace and quiet of the countryside.
I am a lover of tiles and ceramics in general and in the next life I want to learn to work on the lathe.
I do not like to "travel" but "stay" in places, in fact, in every place I visited, every trip I've done I've always lived in a house, never in hotels, places to live and do not visit them.
Good life to everyone!

 For this reason changeover day usually is on Saturday. In low season or if there is no subsequent booking we are happy to make exceptions. Guests leaving are asked to check out by 10am. Guests arriving are asked to arrive after 3pm.

name: vintage nice flat in Rome up to 7 people!
summary: A vintage, big, confortable, full equipped flat, up to 7 people, to enjoy the experience of Italian life in a classic way, in a central and well connected area of Roma. Buses at 5 minutes, metro at 10 minutes, city trains at 15 minutes, walk to the Colosseum in less than 30 minutes. Night buses too! Easy to reach from airports. Very quiet, safe and not touristical area, full of not expensive bars, restaurants, shops. Very big and wonderful park at 5 minutes, with Roman ruins inside.
space: Two double rooms in an original Italian vintage home that was my granparents'! Almost all the decorations and the furniture is original to feel back in the 60's! The beds are very comfortable, the rooms are very quiet, overlooking on an internal courtyard. Your pets, if friendly, are welcome (ask me). IMPORTANT: the double beds are for 4 people, but there is a bunk bed in one room and I can add a foldable single bed in the other room to host up to 7 people with an extra of only €15 per night per person. NOTE ABOUT HEATING: The heating is centralized from the building and because of municipality laws it can be on only from the 15th of November to 15th of Avril and only from 6AM to 8 AM and from 3 PM to 10 PM.  Wear warm clothes if you are a cold person!

neighborhood_overview: I live in an area pretty close to the center! You can walk to the archeological area (Colosseo, Circo Massimo, Appia Antica, Caracalla bath, Aurelian walls). There are many shops and restaurants around. There is also a big park very close when you can relax!
notes: You can bring your pets, I will like to know them too! In the house there will be all you need for them. You can free them in the whole house.
transit: With a ten minutes walk you can reach the metro that takes you to the center and to Vatican-San Pietro. At few metres there are buses that go to the archeological and Renaissance center and to the main railways station. At 1.5 km there are city railway lines that go to Fiumicino Airport, to the beach, to Ostia Antica, to lake Bracciano, to Cerveteri's necropolis. I am very well linked to the place where you will arrive in Rome! To reach home from main railway station Termini there is A metro line (only 4 stops, 1 km from home) or a direct bus. To reach home from Fiumicino airport there is a train that stops a Roma Tuscolana (1,5 km from home), or another train that goes to Termini station and cheaper buses that goes to Termini station as well. To reach the house from Ciampino airport there are buses that reach the A metro line (Anagina stop) that brings to my home, or buses that goes to Termini station.
access: You can use a full equipped kitchen (fridge, gas cooker, electric oven, microwave, toaster, kettle, etc) when you can cook your meals and eat them! Or you can eat in the big dining room, where you can also relax or chat with your friends. The bathroom is shared with your friends so please consider this in using it (for timing and cleanliness). Please also don't take too long showers. There is unlimited wi-fi access to the internet in the house! The washing machine is €5 for each use. I will do it for you. I cannot include breakfast in my offer (always because of the italian law) but you can cook your own! Check-in is after 4 p.m., check out is before 12 a.m., please respect these times. Normally I cannot change these times because I have guests before you and after you, but maybe you could leave your luggage before or after check-in or check-out (ask me in advance). If you want to be sure to be able to do an early check-in or a late check-out simply book another nights before or after
interaction: With pleasure we will meet at the check in, I will give you a free map of Roma, I will show you the house, let you sign a contract  for the staying (necessary for italian law) and ask you for your details because I have to send them to the italian government. If you need to leave your luggage before check-in time you could do it from 12 PM, ask me in advance to be sure it will be possible. If you will need to leave your luggage for some hours after the check-out we have to agree how, ask me in advance to be sure it will be possibile. If you came late at night (after 8 PM) I will let you find the keys without me being there. I live in a very close house, so if you need some help you can call me with the house phone. If you would like to interact more, I will be glad to know you better, do something together and maybe make friendship ! :-)
house_rules: Don't break anything! Always close the windows when you exit. Don't open the front door to anyone that you don't know. Check-in is after 4 p.m., check out is before 12 a.m.  Don't be too noisy for the neighbours, especially at night. Don't lose the keys. Try to have fun! :-D
host_about:
My name is Alfredo, I was born in Rome and I always lived here. 
I'm a normal guy that doesn't accept to be normal, so very soon I make a mess in my life. 
I am open minded and very curios, I can be very shy and people say that I look very gentle and peaceful. 
I try to always see things from another point of view, but I can be also very lazy in doing real stuff. 
I have a lot of interests but I am also dispersive. 
I can be very simple and very complicated: I have lot of contradictions and doubts! :-)
I am antifascist, antiraxist, antisexist and antispecist. 
I think everyone must be free and alive so I don't eat animal and I don't eat or use anything that comes from animals: someone would say I am vegan. :-) 
I like to read, photography, to spend time on computers, to cook, to eat, to drink, to meet strange people, to love, to relax on the beach, to trekking on mountains, animals, to walk. 

******************
Mi chiamo Alfredo, sono nato a Roma e sempre vissuto qui.
Sono un ragazzo normale a cui non piace la normalità, quindi spesso faccio un casino nella vita.
Sono di mentalità aperta e molto curioso, posso essere molto timido e dicono che sembro molto gentile e pacioso.
Cerco sempre di vedere le cose da un altro punto di vista, ma posso anche essere molto pigro nell'attivarmi.
Ho molti interessi ma sono anche dispersivo.
Posso essere molto semplice e molto complicato: ho un sacco di contraddizioni e dubbi! :-)
Sono antifascista, antirazzista, antisessista e antispecista.
Penso che tutti debbano essere liberi e vivi quindi non mangio animali e non mangio o uso niente che viene dagli animali: qualcuno potrebbe dire che sono vegano. :-)
Mi piace leggere, la fotografia, perdere tempo al pc, cucinare, mangiare, bere, incontrare persone strane, amare, rilassarmi sulla spiaggia, fare trekking in montagna, gli animali, viaggiare.

You will still have fantastic access to businesses, markets, bakeries, and restaurants. There are some famous restaurants/bakery few minutes walk from the house: Bareburger, Artichoke Pizza, Brooklyn Bagel &Coffee Company, Taverna Kyclades, Martha Country Bakery.
notes: Myself and Anthony love to interact with people. We would be more than happy to give you list of restaurants, bars, list of museums, parks, clubs and broadway shows worth seeing in New York. Mon compagnon et moi habitons à New York dans le quartier de Ditmars Astoria, Queens. Nous sommes situés à seulement 15 min de Manhattan en métro (le métro marche 24h/24). Ditmars est un quartier vivant et multiculturel, plein de restaurants, bars, commerces, laveries.. Si c'est votre première visite à New York, nous serons ravis de partager bons plans et autres activités sympas à faire à New York! Hola! Soy francesa-peruana. Hablo frances y español. Si se sienten mas comodo communicar en español avisanme :)
transit: The apartment is at walking distance from the N train- Ditmars Blvd station. It is convenient and direct to Manhattan. There are also plenty of taxis at the train station. It takes 15min to get to Manhattan.  Ditmars is very close from Laguardia Airport- 10min about 16 and 30min from JFK in taxi about 35.
access: The guests have access to the entire apartment and its balcony. It is an independent apartment with a separate entrance.
interaction: The hosts live close by to the apartment and are always available if needed. The hosts will be greeting the guests at check in. The hosts are reachable via airbnb email or phone for any questions.
house_rules: No Smoking Noise should be low after 10 pm as our neighbors are elderly people and we do not want any complains. Check out before noon. We are flexible for the check- in after 3pm.

host_about:
Two professionals in New York City, myself, originally from France and my fiancee Anthony originally from Nepal. We both love to travel, we love trying different authentic cuisines and we like to learn about different cultures. Me and my Anthony have so far travelled to Netherlands, France, Spain, Belgium, Greece, Germany, Italy, England, Sweden, Czech Republic, Morocco, Tunisia, Peru, Puerto rico, Bahamas, Mexico, Costa Rica, Canada,Dubai, Turkey, Nepal and India.

However for us “In terms of worldwide international cities, New York City is the best.”

My fiancée speaks Nepali fluently and I am French and I speak French, Spanish and English fluently. I have couple of listing New York City and a place in Kathmandu Nepal listed on AIR BNB and on Home Away site.

Anthony's hobby beside traveling includes playing Soccer, Golfing, Surfing, biking, jazz music, watching musicals, broadway shows, visiting art galleries and I enjoy Salsa Dancing, hiking, arts, museums, biking and skiing.

Motto: "Treat others in the same manner as you would like to be treated"

name: COSY APARTMENT IN LA LATINA
summary: A fantastic two-bedroom apartment located right in the centre of Madrid in a popular area known as "La Latina", in the historic quarter of the city and within walking distance of landmarks like the Royal Palace, the Almudena Cathedral, the Royal Theatre (Opera House), the Plaza Mayor and Puerta del Sol.
space: The apartment is on the third floor (no lift!!!) of a renovated 19th Century house. The apartment itself was also fully renovated and re-decorated recently. It has two bedrooms (currently only one bedroom is available), a living/dining room, kitchen and small shower room. It is an "interior" apartment, meaning that the windows do not overlook the street but rather an inner communal court or patio. This means that the apartment is very quiet at night as you do not hear the noise from the many nearby bars and pubs. The apartment is small but cosy. It is suitable for single travellers or couples. Blankets and bed linen are provided. No smoking is allowed in the apartment, and no pets, sorry.

neighborhood_overview: a Latina is a cool and trendy area with a lively atmosphere and a bohemian-like feel. It is very pleasant in the day and you can just walk around the narrow cobbled streets and discover the history of the city, from ancient Arab times to the so-called “Madrid de los Austrias”, Madrid's Mediaeval quarter. It is also the place to go for tapas, especially on Sunday afternoon but the place is also bustling on Friday and Saturday night, when young Spaniards and foreigners alike fill the many pubs, restaurants and tapas bars.
transit: La Latina metro (underground) station is just 2 minutes walk and buses also stop in the area, including the touristic double-decker buses. Plenty of taxis are also available but the truth is that, being so central, you can just walk to virtually anywhere in the centre of Madrid, from Gran Vía, Plaza de España and the Temple of Debod to Retiro Park, Cibeles and Casa de Campo.
access: L
interaction: I am available for my guests at any time on Airbnb's chat option and I always strive to answer to enquiries as soon as possible.
house_rules: - Respetar a los demás vecinos del inmueble y las normas de convivencia.
host_about:
I am a Spanish man based in Madrid. I was born and raised in Spain but I also lived in the UK for several years where I graduated in Linguistics at the University of Manchester. I work as a translator and interpreter and I also run a small translation business in Madrid. I love my job as it gives me the opportunity to do some of the things I like most: talking and communicating, meeting people and travelling around the world. 

I love languages: I am bilingual in Spanish and English and I can also speak French and Arabic. I am particularly interested in Arabic language and culture. I have been studying Arabic since 2007, mainly in Spain but also in Arab countries like Tunisia, Egypt and Jordan. I have also been to other countries in North Africa, the Middle East and the Gulf (Morocco, Jordan, Lebanon, Iraq, Kuwait and Qatar). 

Finally, I am educated, mature, approachable, respectful and easygoing, and I enjoy a good conversation over a coffee or a dinner party at home as much as going out and clubbing.
street: La Latina, Madrid, Comunidad de Madrid 28005, Spain

host_about:
In the heart of Ealing, known as Queen of suburbs, The Caspian offers cosy rooms with continental breakfast in a friendly family environment. We have been serving the local and international community for decades and the hospitality of The Caspian has not diminished over these years.


Caspian is conveniently nestled on the corner of Haven Green. Set in a Victorian Era house, all rooms are double glazed with TV, free WIFI and seating area provided. Some rooms have period features and large windows with garden view.

We offer a large variety of rooms: diversified by their size, colour and price.

We have onsite parking and a meeting room is available for hire. It offers a pleasant ambiance for board meetings or private reunions.





The Caspian is a 2 minutes’ walk from Ealing Broadway Station and 15 minutes from Central London. Ealing Broadway shopping centres, restaurants and all amenities are a short walk. Our sister La Baguette coffee shop/restaurant offers delicious Tunisian and international food (10% discount for Hotel guests). 

So much is going on in Ealing: Ealing Summer Festivals (Jazz, Blues, Comedy, Beer, Carnival) in July, Ealing Half Marathon in September.
 ...and around Ealing: Sport and Music events at Wembley Stadium all year, and the unique grand Westfield Shopping Malls is a short bus or train ride. The significant Walpole Park along with Pitzhanger Manor are a short stroll from Caspian.

Caspian Hotel is just 20 minutes’ drive from Heathrow Airport. The M4, M40 and A406 motorways are only 5 minutes’ drive.





The Caspian has been visited by top consultant Alex Polizzi from The Hotel Inspector TV Series on 3 consecutive years.

host_about:
Fabio De Benedettis was born in Rome in 1969.
In 1998, he moved to London where he worked until 2002, first as an assistant to Sergio Bondioni-portrait photographer then to Paul Pannack-fashion photographer before becoming a freelancer, dealing with conceptual photography and portraiture. In 2000 he graduated in photography at Stanmore College of Art in London.

He currently works as a freelance producing predominantly social reportage. He has worked in over 25 countries including Bosnia, Kosovo, Serbia, Slovenia, Croatia, Turkey, Western Sahara, Algeria, Tunisia, Egypt, Nigeria, Kenya, Seychelles, India, Ireland, England, Denmark, Sweden, France, Spain, Germany and the Netherlands.
Has partnered with many NGO, NATO, the UN and several Italian journalists.

Parallel to his activities as a photographer grew his personal artistic research and the creation of conceptual photography. He has exhibited in several group shows and solo in Italy, China, UK, Argentina, Germany and Singapore.

IMPORTANT: the double bed is for 2 people, but I can put a folding bed in your room to host another person with an extra of only €15 per night. NOTE ABOUT HEATING: The heating is centralized fro
neighborhood_overview: I live in an area pretty close to the center! You can walk to the archeological area (Colosseo, Circo Massimo, Appia Antica, Caracalla bath, Aurelian walls). There are many shops and restaurants around. There is also a big park very close when you can relax!
notes: You can bring your pets, I will like to know them too! In the house there will be all you need for them. They should always be kept in your room, unless you book the two rooms of the house or you ask to the other guests.
transit: With a ten minutes walk you can reach the metro that takes you to the center and to Vatican-San Pietro. At few metres there are buses that go to the archeological and Renaissance center and to the main railways station. At 1.5 km there are city railway lines that go to Fiumicino Airport, to the beach, to Ostia Antica, to lake Bracciano, to Cerveteri's necropolis. I am very well linked to the place where you will arrive in Rome! To reach home from main railway station Termini there is A metro line (only 4 stops, 1 km from home) or a direct bus. To reach home from Fiumicino airport there is a train that stops a Roma Tuscolana (1,5 km from home), or another train that goes to Termini station and cheaper buses that goes to Termini station as well. To reach the house from Ciampino airport there are buses that reach the A metro line (Anagina stop) that brings to my home, or buses that goes to Termini station.
access: You can use a full equipped kitchen (fridge, gas cooker, electric oven, microwave, toaster, kettle, etc) when you can cook your meals and eat them! Or you can eat in the big dining room, where you can also relax or chat with the other guests. The bathroom is shared with the other guests that can be other 4 people (unless you book the whole flat) so please consider this in using it (for timing and cleanliness). Please also don't take too long showers. While you are here, I will clean as often as I can the common area (because of italian law I cannot clean your room). There is unlimited wi-fi access to the internet in the house! The washing machine is €5 for each use. I will do it for you. I cannot include breakfast in my offer (always because of the italian law) but you can cook your own! Check-in is after 4 p.m., check out is before 12 a.m., please respect these times. Normally I cannot change these times because I have guests before you and after you, but maybe you could leave your lu
interaction: With pleasure we will meet at the check in, I will give you a free map of Roma, I will show you the house, let you sign a contract  for the staying (necessary for italian law) and ask you for your details because I have to send them to the italian government. If you need to leave your luggage before check-in time you could do it from 12 PM, ask me in advance to be sure it will be possible. If you will need to leave your luggage for some hours after the check-out we have to agree how, ask me in advance to be sure it will be possibile. If you came late at night (after 8 PM) I will let you find the keys without me being there. I live in a very close house, so if you need some help you can call me with the house phone. If you would like to interact more, I will be glad to know you better, do something together and maybe make friendship ! :-)
house_rules: Non rompere niente! Chiudi sempre le finestre quando esci. Non aprire la porta di casa ad estranei. Il check-in è dalle 16, il check-out è entro le 12. Non disturbare i vicini, specialmente di notte. Non passare troppo tempo nel bagno condiviso e risparmia energia per la Terra. Non perdere le chiavi. Divertiti! :-D
host_about:
My name is Alfredo, I was born in Rome and I always lived here. 
I'm a normal guy that doesn't accept to be normal, so very soon I make a mess in my life. 
I am open minded and very curios, I can be very shy and people say that I look very gentle and peaceful. 
I try to always see things from another point of view, but I can be also very lazy in doing real stuff. 
I have a lot of interests but I am also dispersive. 
I can be very simple and very complicated: I have lot of contradictions and doubts! :-)
I am antifascist, antiraxist, antisexist and antispecist. 
I think everyone must be free and alive so I don't eat animal and I don't eat or use anything that comes from animals: someone would say I am vegan. :-) 
I like to read, photography, to spend time on computers, to cook, to eat, to drink, to meet strange people, to love, to relax on the beach, to trekking on mountains, animals, to walk. 

******************
Mi chiamo Alfredo, sono nato a Roma e sempre vissuto qui.
Sono un ragazzo normale a cui non piace la normalità, quindi spesso faccio un casino nella vita.
Sono di mentalità aperta e molto curioso, posso essere molto timido e dicono che sembro molto gentile e pacioso.
Cerco sempre di vedere le cose da un altro punto di vista, ma posso anche essere molto pigro nell'attivarmi.
Ho molti interessi ma sono anche dispersivo.
Posso essere molto semplice e molto complicato: ho un sacco di contraddizioni e dubbi! :-)
Sono antifascista, antirazzista, antisessista e antispecista.
Penso che tutti debbano essere liberi e vivi quindi non mangio animali e non mangio o uso niente che viene dagli animali: qualcuno potrebbe dire che sono vegano. :-)
Mi piace leggere, la fotografia, perdere tempo al pc, cucinare, mangiare, bere, incontrare persone strane, amare, rilassarmi sulla spiaggia, fare trekking in montagna, gli animali, viaggiare.

neighborhood_overview: Ditmars, Astoria is a vibrant neighborhood. There are plenty of restaurants and stores walking distance from the studio (2 blocks away) Artichoke pizzeria, Greek restaurants, Japanese, starbucks etc.. The studio is also walking distance from Astoria park. Ditmars area is a diverse neighborhood. It has both the feel of a bustling commercial area and a residential vibe. You will still have fantastic access to businesses, markets, bakeries, and restaurants. There are some famous restaurants/bakery few minutes walk from the house: Bareburger, Artichoke Pizza, Brooklyn Bagel &Coffee Company, Taverna Kyclades, Martha Country Bakery.
notes: Myself and Anthony love to interact with people. We would be more than happy to give you list of restaurants, bars, list of museums, parks, clubs and broadway shows worth seeing in New York.  We will do everything we can to make your stay comfortable and to make you feel that you are living in a home away from home. I am from France and i speak French, Spanish and English and Anthony speak Nepalese, Hindi and English. Bonjour! Je m'appelle Laura. Je suis française. Mon compagnon et moi habitons à New York dans le quartier de Ditmars Astoria, Queens. Nous sommes situés à seulement 15 min de Manhattan en métro (le métro marche 24h/24). Ditmars est un quartier vivant et multiculturel, plein de restaurants, bars, commerces, laveries.. Si c'est votre première visite à New York, nous serons ravis de partager bons plans et autres activités sympas à faire à New York! Hola! Soy francesa-peruana. Hablo frances y español. Si se sienten mas comodo communicar en español avisanme :)
transit: The studio is 2 blocks away from the N train line which takes you directly to Manhattan: 59th str & Lexington Ave., Central Park and Times Square. Getting around: The apartment is at walking distance from the N train- Ditmars Blvd station. It is convenient and direct to Manhattan. There are also plenty of taxis at the train station. It takes 15min to get to Manhattan.  Ditmars is very close from Laguardia Airport- 10min about 16 and 30min from JFK in taxi about 35.
access: The guests have access to the entire studio, and the backyard deck. The guests can also have access to the dryer and washer.
interaction: The hosts live right above. We will greet the guests at arrival and we are available anytime if guests have questions.
house_rules: No smoking allowed in the house. Check in after 3 pm Check out before noon No overnight guest allowed for sleep over, only for guest who have booked the place.

host_about:
Two professionals in New York City, myself, originally from France and my fiancee Anthony originally from Nepal. We both love to travel, we love trying different authentic cuisines and we like to learn about different cultures. Me and my Anthony have so far travelled to Netherlands, France, Spain, Belgium, Greece, Germany, Italy, Netherland, Portugal, Sweden, Finland, Estonia, England, Sweden, Czech Republic, Morocco, Tunisia, Peru, Puerto rico, Bahamas, Mexico, Costa Rica, Canada,Dubai, Turkey, Nepal and India.

However for us “In terms of worldwide international cities, New York City is the best.”

My fiancée speaks Nepali fluently and I am French and I speak French, Spanish and English fluently. I have couple of listing New York City and a place in Kathmandu Nepal listed on AIR BNB and on Home Away site.

Anthony's hobby beside traveling includes playing Soccer, Golfing, Surfing, biking, watching musicals, broadway shows, visiting art galleries and I enjoy Salsa Dancing, hiking, arts, biking and skiing.

Motto: "Treat others in the same manner as you would like to be treated"

host_about:
I have lived in London for 6 years. I have been exploring – and still I do- all corners of this city and I love discover new spots all times but I am happy to be back home in SW where is my home. I adore enjoying the relaxed atmosphere of local cafes and pubs of my neighbourhoods, its international life and its traditional architecture. I am from the south of Italy, no doubts I love good food and wine. Though I love cooking, I adore the incredible selection of restaurants and street food London offers.
I can’t live without my music (jazz, soul, bossanova and opera) and time to time I treat myself with a concert or gig - London is offers the best choice of music, theatre and arts!
I love sports and I am closed to some of the most beautiful London’s parks and the Thames bank where I can enjoy a relaxing stroll as well as a good run. Travelling is my greatest passion. I have lived in the north and the south of Italy, in Belgium and Tunisia and I brought with me bits of them. I have been travelling in America, Africa and Asia and it is time to make the most of living in such a beautiful part of the world: Europe!

name: ROOM 12.BED&BREAKFAST CASPIAN HOTEL
summary: Room 12 FAMILY SUITE. 5 people. 2 double beds and 1 single bed. With breakfast.  Minimum 2 nights.
description: Room 12 FAMILY SUITE. 5 people. 2 double beds and 1 single bed. With breakfast.  Minimum 2 nights.
host_about:
In the heart of Ealing, known as Queen of suburbs, The Caspian offers cosy rooms with continental breakfast in a friendly family environment. We have been serving the local and international community for decades and the hospitality of The Caspian has not diminished over these years.


Caspian is conveniently nestled on the corner of Haven Green. Set in a Victorian Era house, all rooms are double glazed with TV, free WIFI and seating area provided. Some rooms have period features and large windows with garden view.

We offer a large variety of rooms: diversified by their size, colour and price.

We have onsite parking and a meeting room is available for hire. It offers a pleasant ambiance for board meetings or private reunions.





The Caspian is a 2 minutes’ walk from Ealing Broadway Station and 15 minutes from Central London. Ealing Broadway shopping centres, restaurants and all amenities are a short walk. Our sister La Baguette coffee shop/restaurant offers delicious Tunisian and international food (10% discount for Hotel guests). 

So much is going on in Ealing: Ealing Summer Festivals (Jazz, Blues, Comedy, Beer, Carnival) in July, Ealing Half Marathon in September.
 ...and around Ealing: Sport and Music events at Wembley Stadium all year, and the unique grand Westfield Shopping Malls is a short bus or train ride. The significant Walpole Park along with Pitzhanger Manor are a short stroll from Caspian.

Caspian Hotel is just 20 minutes’ drive from Heathrow Airport. The M4, M40 and A406 motorways are only 5 minutes’ drive.





The Caspian has been visited by top consultant Alex Polizzi from The Hotel Inspector TV Series on 3 consecutive years.
street: The Broadway, London, W5, United Kingdom

The place can accommodate 2 people perfectly, and also a baby (I have a small bed for babies).

neighborhood_overview: The Verdun's neighbourhood is perfect for a Montreal's vacation. It is quiet and secure, and 8 minutes in subway from downtown. The subway is just one minute away. There are lots of really good restaurants nearby (I'll give you a map of the neighbourhood that I made to guide you with the nice places) , cafes, bar, and boutiques. The St-Lawrence river is about 5 minutes by walk from the condo, and it is really nice to walk there in the summer. There is a bicycle path that leads you directly to the old Montreal in 20 minutes (bike), you can swim, rent kayak, or just walk. It is really nice there, and during the winter some people do ski.
notes: I'll leave you maps of Montreal if you need it!
transit: It is around 20 minutes by car form the airport (around 35 CAD  in cab) or 7 by bus to the closest subway station (Lionel-Groulx). Then you'll have to take the subway for 3 stations. There is also free parking in the street if you are coming by car.
host_about:
Bonjour! je m'appelle Laurence et j'adore mon quartier et Montréal!! Je travaille dans le domaine de l'emploi   et j'ai fait des études en anthropologie et en commerce international.  Je  suis une passionnée des voyages, de la lecture (des romans à l'eau de rose au documentaire) et du cinéma! J'adore rencontrer des gens d'ailleurs et en apprendre plus sur leur cultures et coutumes.  J'ai d'ailleurs passé une année  en Argentine dans le cadre de mes études, expérience que  j'ai adoré !! Je reviens récemment du Pérou et prévois aller prochainement au Japon et c'est une des raisons pour laquelle je souhaite louer mon appartement! J'ai également voyagé en Europe, Chine et Tunisie mais j'avoue que mon coup de coeur demeure l'Amérique du Sud, et plus particulièrement la Bolivie! 
Je suis très accueillante et amicale, et j'adore faire plaisir aux gens et leur faire de petites attentions spéciales. Je vous laisserai toujours des brochures, cartes et livres sur la ville pour que vous puissiez plus facilement vous retrouver. Je serai tout près de l'appartement, ( chez mon copain, à moins de 5 minutes à pied)  durant votre séjour si vous avez des questions ou autre.  
Je parle couramment le français, l'anglais et l'espagnol et je serais ravie de vous donner des conseils touristiques sur mon quartier et ma ville! Mon appartement est  très accueillant et je suis sûre que vous apprécierez votre séjour chez moi! 

----------
Hi! My name is Laurence and really love my neighbourhood and Montreal!! I am currently working in the employment field  and  I graduated in anthropology and international commerce.  I am   passionnate about travels, reading  and cinema!  I love to meet people from all over the world and learn more about the culture. I lived one year abroad in Argentina and just loved it! I just came back from Peru and I'm thinking about going to Japan in few months, which is one of the reason why I want to rent my place! I also went to China, Europe and Tunisie, but my favorite place is South America, especially Bolivia!
You always will find in my house a little gift for you, flyers and maps of the town !
 I speak French, English and Spanish and I would be more than happy to give you more  information and tips about my city and  neighbourhood!
During your stay, I will live less than 5 minutes from the appartment if you have any doubt or questions. 
My appartment is really homy and I am pretty sure  that you will really enjoy it as much as I do!  I am looking forward to meeting you!
street: Rue Gordon, Montréal, Québec H4G 2R3, Canada

neighborhood_overview: If there's any area of San Francisco that evokes images of the long-gone '60s hippie culture, the Haight is it. Fragments of that flower-power, incense-burning, acid-dropping, tie-dye-wearing, peace-and-love-vibing era can be purchased at smoke shops and Eastern-influenced outlets bearing names like Dreams of Kathmandu and The Love of Ganesha. But save for a few hippie relics, the Haight today is a whole new scene. Exclusive boutiques, high-end vintage-clothing shops, second-hand stores, Internet cafés and hip restaurants have all settled in, making the Haight one of San Francisco's commercial centers.

host_about:
My name is Alfredo, I was born in Rome and I always lived here. 
I'm a normal guy that doesn't accept to be normal, so very soon I make a mess in my life. 
I am open minded and very curios, I can be very shy and people say that I look very gentle and peaceful. 
I try to always see things from another point of view, but I can be also very lazy in doing real stuff. 
I have a lot of interests but I am also dispersive. 
I can be very simple and very complicated: I have lot of contradictions and doubts! :-)
I am antifascist, antiraxist, antisexist and antispecist. 
I think everyone must be free and alive so I don't eat animal and I don't eat or use anything that comes from animals: someone would say I am vegan. :-) 
I like to read, photography, to spend time on computers, to cook, to eat, to drink, to meet strange people, to love, to relax on the beach, to trekking on mountains, animals, to walk. 

******************
Mi chiamo Alfredo, sono nato a Roma e sempre vissuto qui.
Sono un ragazzo normale a cui non piace la normalità, quindi spesso faccio un casino nella vita.
Sono di mentalità aperta e molto curioso, posso essere molto timido e dicono che sembro molto gentile e pacioso.
Cerco sempre di vedere le cose da un altro punto di vista, ma posso anche essere molto pigro nell'attivarmi.
Ho molti interessi ma sono anche dispersivo.
Posso essere molto semplice e molto complicato: ho un sacco di contraddizioni e dubbi! :-)
Sono antifascista, antirazzista, antisessista e antispecista.
Penso che tutti debbano essere liberi e vivi quindi non mangio animali e non mangio o uso niente che viene dagli animali: qualcuno potrebbe dire che sono vegano. :-)
Mi piace leggere, la fotografia, perdere tempo al pc, cucinare, mangiare, bere, incontrare persone strane, amare, rilassarmi sulla spiaggia, fare trekking in montagna, gli animali, viaggiare.

host_about:
Ciao !
Se state leggendo la mia descrizione, quasi sicuramente avete intenzione di soggiornare a Roma;
Magari proprio nel mio appartamento, perciò trovo giusto che iniziate a conoscermi un pò meglio :
Ho finito il mio percorso di studi laureandomi in scienze politiche e sin da subito ho deciso di orientarmi nel settore immobiliare\turismo.
Mi piace molto leggere, informarmi e migliorarmi sempre di più, proprio per questo mi piace molto la condivisione  e il confronto con l'altro.
Adoro Roma per la sua storia e le bellezze che offre;
motivo per cui ho deciso di condividere le mie conoscenze su questa meravigliosa città con con i miei ospiti. 
Mi piace moltissimo viaggiare, sono stato a in Inghilterra, Spagna, Francia,Svizzera,Ungheria,Tunisia ecc...
Ma il mio sogno nel cassetto è visitare l'America !!!
Sono inoltre un grande amante della cucina, perciò non vedo l'ora di consigliarvi i miei ristoranti preferiti !!!
Ps: Ricordate che sono a vostra completa disposizione, non esitate a chiedermi qualsiasi informazione, qualsiasi tipo richiesta la risolveremo insieme.

-Follow Your Dreams-


Hello !
If you are reading my description, probably you will want to come to stay in Rome;
Maybe in my apartment, so I find that is a good idea start to know me a little better:
I finished my course of studies graduating in political science, and right now I decided to get my bearings in real estate \ tourism.
I enjoy reading, always inform and improve myself more, for this reason I really like sharing and comparing with each other.
I love Rome for its history and beauty that offers;
In fact I decided to share my knowledge of this wonderful city with my guests.
I love traveling, I have been in England, Spain, France, Switzerland, Hungary, Tunisia etc ...
But my dream is to visit America !!!
They are also a great lover of the Italian kitchen so I'll be very happy to recommend my favorite restaurants !!!
PS: Remember i'm at your disposal, do not hesitate to ask me any information, any request we will solve it together.

-Follow Your Dreams-

L'immeuble est résidentiel, très calme, habité par des vénitiens. Je suis flexible pour les arrivées et les départs, à concorder ensemble. Cleaning lady is coming at the end of your stay around 14h00. La femme de ménage passe en fin de séjour vers 14h l'après-midi. Mind to bring down the garbage bag between 6h and 8h AM, in compliance with the Venetian municipal rules. host_about:
I happen to be a mining engineer and an amateur historian with a focus on Venice and its region. Although I have been living in this city for the past 17 years, I always find something new to discover at an unexpected spot.

I am also an avid traveler first by choice and then by profession, as I have been working in more than ten countries (Bulgaria, Serbia, Montenegro, Macedonia Turkey, Cyprus, Vietnam, Algeria, Tunisia,  Egypt, Jordan, Saudi Arabia, Uganda, Ivory Coast, South Africa, Cape Verde, France) for the last 5 years.

Above all, meeting new people is always an excitement for me. When in Venice, it is my pleasure trying to pass them as much cultural and practical knowledge  of the city as I can.

name: Great apartment at the Lido center
summary: Large 3 bedrooms apartment 145 m2  with a private garden  in a Liberty Art Nouveau villa, at the center of Lido, 5 minutes away from the beaches and 15 minutes from Saint-Mark's Square.
space: The apartment is located in an Art Nouveau - Liberty style - villa built around 1910 at the center of Lido. It is close to the beaches and abotu 15 minutes away to Piazza San Marco at the very heart of Venice. This situation is a key advantage, as it is possible both to visit this great Art city which is Venice with its monuments and to enjoy a sea vacation on the nearby Adriatic beaches. Or simply to relax in the garden, where one can have lunch or diner. It is a great place for whoever has a large family or a group of friends. It is possible to accommodate up to 9 persons, and, if needed, even larger groups up to 18 people thanks to another apartment at the floor below in the same villa.

neighborhood_overview: The Lido has kept an unique turn-of-the-century, charm, with a lot of 1900 villas dominated by large Edwardian style hotels such as the Excelsior and the Des Bains. This cosmopolitan atmosphere, still alive, is well described in Luigi Visconti's movie "Death in Venice" (from Thomas Mann's novel) or in Lord Norwich's book "Paradise of cities" or in some Dona Leon's crime stories. In summer time, the Lido is a sea-side town, with crowded sandy beaches, five minutes away in vaporetto from the historical heart of Venice. In spring time, it is a perfect place where to rest after strolling Venice.
notes: Un appartement identique à l'étage au dessus permet d'accueillir 9 personnes supplémentaires le cas échéant.
transit: The Lido is well deserved by public transport as it is connected to:  - the airport with a vaporetto each half hour - the trip lasts about an hour.  - Venice with a vaporetto each 8 minutes during daytime and each 20 minutes during the night, from (phone number hidden);  - the mainland - through Jesolo and Punta Sabbioni each hour. It is also possible to drive, although you would need to take the ferry at the Tronchetto terminal in Venice. There is a network of bus, bringing people to the secluded Murazzi beaches and to Pallestrina along the coast. It is also easy to rent bikes (including tandem) to explore this golden island.
access: Guests would have a 145 m2 apartment, with 3 bedrooms, a large living-room with an entrance hall, a kitchen, 2 bathrooms, a sunny terrace and a garden.
interaction: As the author of guide books on Venice, the Lido and Venetian Istria and Dalmatia, I usually try to do my best to advise my guests on how to live as a Venetian.

Une règle impérative est de descendre les déchets seulement entre 6h et 8h le matin, en conformité avec le règlement municipal.

host_about:
I am a (retired) emeritus professor of theatre and performing arts at the University of Rome, where I worked for  47 years and also directed a research center on performing arts for 30 years, travelling and shooting documentary films in Marocco, Tunisia, Somalia, Kenya, India, Pakistan, Sri Lanka, Seychelles, Burma, Cambodia, Japan, Cina, Bali, Brazil, Columbia, Mexico, and the Caribbean. I love to give tips and talk about the places I visited to my friends, my Airbnb guests and pretty much anyone who asks or is willing to listen :) I am an avid reader, adore the arts and trying new foods and absolutely love my beautiful dogs Titto and Bella! As an experienced traveller myself, in being a host I am attentive and always go the extra mile for my guests.

My quote of the day: "Man cannot discover new oceans if he does not have the courage to distance himself from the coast".

name: Lovely apartment in Testaccio
summary: My house is a lovely  and bright apartment  in  an old building located in the district "Testaccio".  Testaccio is an  historical district of ancient Rome which takes the name from the artificial  mound composed  entirely of Roman anphoras sherds.
space: My house is a lovely  and bright apartment  on the fourth floor of an old building located in the district "Testaccio".  Testaccio is an  historical district of ancient Rome which takes the name from the artificial  mound composed  entirely of "testae" (Italian: cocci), fragments of broken amphorae dating from the times  of the Roman Empire! From my house you can see the amazing little hill of sherds which is unique in the world. The house is a cozy  and bright apartment perfect for a single traveler or a family of max four members.  It is composed by one bedroom with a double bed, a big living room with a bed sofa, a lovely fully furnished kitchen and 1 bathroom with shower. There is also a  little studio corner with the internet access. As I am an archaeologist and  I like traveling,  the house forniture comes mainly from my trips in Marocco, Tunisia and orient so is quite ethnic in  style and very coloured!  The house is fully furnished including washing machine and bed linen.
description: My house is a lovely  and bright apartment  in  an old building located in the district "Testaccio".  Testaccio is an  historical district of ancient Rome which takes the name from the artificial  mound composed  entirely of Roman anphoras sherds.
neighborhood_overview: The district Testaccio is a very typical  and characteristic historical district of Rome close to the Tiber river. It's very popular for its lively and coloured  food market  where you can find  the traditional genuine Roman  food and many streetfoodsshops. The district it's also famous for it's typical traditional Roman cuisine restaurants.
notes: Testaccio has also many historical sights to visit as it was the ancient port of Rome:  the "Monte dei Cocci" or Mound of the sherds, the protestant cemetry were the poets Keats and Lord  Bayron where buried and finally the Piramid , a munumental marble Piramid built duiring Roman times.
transit: The district is very well connected to central Rome with the  metro station Piramide at only  5 minutes walking distance and lots of busses to central Rome. 10 minutes walking distance to Trastevere and 15 minutes walking distance to Venice Square.
access: Washing machine, TV, internet , bed sheets, towels.

host_about:
Hello, I am  Petya Hottz. 
Welcome to my great international family in New York. Let me show you around.
I live in a 3 bedroom apartment in Astoria, Queens, with my husband Thiago, who is from Brazil and a Chinese boy Jack. I have a lot of great locations and  of course they are not in the same apartment. Most are in Astoria around us, Woodside, Jackson Heights and  MANHATTAN.  All locations are very nice, clean, well experienced hosting people from all around the world, in pretty convenient and safe  neighborhoods. You are very welcome to be part of my little, international family. 
 I am originally from Bulgaria and I speak English, Bulgarian, Russian, and a little bit of French. I am a very friendly positive person and I am also very open to foreign cultures, music, food, and customs. New York is a very unique city because people are from all around the world and contribute to the diversity of daily living.
As a professional figure skater I have participated in competitions throughout most of Europe. As a child I traveled often with my family to France, Germany, Italy, California, Tunisia and Spain. In addition, I have traveled extensively to North America, Brazil. I love to engage in sports, yoga, tennis, skating, skiing, swimming, hiking, music, dancing and I love to cook. My father and my brother in law are professional chefs. I guess I inherited the passion from them to prepare delicious foods. I would love for you to experience my cuisine.
In addition about my rooms, they all are located in a great neighborhood with restaurants, bars, international food, stores, libraries, parks, schools, shopping malls, and cinemas. Everything is nearby and convenient to public transportation which runs 24 hours a days. It is only 5-25 min to NYC. Or if you need a taxi, they are abundantly available outside the (URL HIDDEN) location is located a block or a few blocks from  subway stations. All rooms are new furnished, AC, WiFi and Cable, all included in the price. I also can offer you occasional free skating classes with me at the local rink.
Welcome to my apartment. I know you are going to feel like you are home. I am waiting for you my new friend. Welcome to New York!

neighborhood_overview: The Lido has kept an unique turn-of-the-century, charm, with a lot of 1900 villas dominated by large Edwardian style hotels such as the Excelsior and the Des Bains. This cosmopolitan atmosphere, still alive,  is well described in Luigi Visconti's movie "Death in Venice" (from Thomas Mann's novel) or in Lord Norwich's book "Paradise of cities" or in some Dona Leon's crime stories.  In summer time, the Lido is a sea-side town, with crowded sandy beaches, five minutes away in vaporetto from the historical heart of Venice. In spring time, it is a perfect place where to rest after  strolling Venice.
notes: Un autre appartement dans la villa permet d'accueillir jusqu'à 9 personnes supplémentaires si besoin.
transit: The Lido is well deserved by public transport as it is connected to: - the airport with a vaporetto each half hour - the trip lasts about an hour. - Venice with a vaporetto each 8 minutes during daytime and each 20 minutes during the night, from 23.00 to 5.00; - the mainland - through Jesolo and Punta Sabbioni each hour. It is also possible to drive, although you would need to take the ferry at the Tronchetto terminal in Venice. There is a network of bus, bringing people to the  secluded Murazzi beaches and to Pallestrina along the coast. It is also easy to rent bikes (including tandem) to explore this golden island.
access: Guests would have a 145 m2 apartment, with 3 bedrooms, a large living-room with an entrance hall, a kitchen, 2 bathrooms, a sunny terrace and a garden.
interaction: As the author of guide books on Venice, the Lido and Venetian Istria and Dalmatia, I usually try to do my best to advise my guests on how to live as a Venetian.
house_rules: J'attends des voyageurs un comportement tranquille, casuel.
host_about:
I happen to be a mining engineer and an amateur historian with a focus on Venice and its region. Although I have been living in this city for the past 17 years, I always find something new to discover at an unexpected spot.

I am also an avid traveler first by choice and then by profession, as I have been working in more than ten countries (Bulgaria, Serbia, Montenegro, Macedonia Turkey, Cyprus, Vietnam, Algeria, Tunisia,  Egypt, Jordan, Saudi Arabia, Uganda, Ivory Coast, South Africa, Cape Verde, France) for the last 5 years.

Above all, meeting new people is always an excitement for me. When in Venice, it is my pleasure trying to pass them as much cultural and practical knowledge  of the city as I can.

name: Luxury Vatican Executive Suite**Jacuzzi**(Ensuite)
summary: Executive Suite with breathtaking view over the Vatican, throughout the overlying Monte Mario district. The Suite has a fabulous Honey Moon Jacuzzi Bath and Ensuite bathroom; the Living space with the pretty open plan kitchenette will allow guests to taste a typical Italian-style breakfast! Ideally located opposite the Vatican Museums and near by all services, it is well connected by public transports for an unforgettable stay!
space: In detail, the Apartment is located in a typical alley right in front of the Vatican Walls and has two entrances: one more easy for luggages at check-in and check-out from Viale Vaticano, as there is no necessity to do stairs, the second access can be used during the stay to reach more quickly the Metro a "Cipro" at 500m from home and also all the neighborhood stores: keep in mind that there is a stairway to reach the main road with all the services, but it allows you to avoid walk along the Vatican Walls lengthening the route, however, in both cases, some gym is assured! In case you do not want to walk or tiring too, all buses going towards the major attractions of Rome (Historic Center, Piazza Navona, Colosseum etc..) passes on Viale Vaticano near the easier access to the flat!
