neighborhood_overview: As described the location is perfect to visit the Vatican Museums and St. Peter's Basilica. You can take a nice walk during the day and also in the evening being a very quiet neighborhood. In 10 minutes you can reach the metro Cipro, through the steps that connect us to the main street with all the services, where you can find restaurants, cafes, shops and all that might be needed for your stay.
notes: The City Tax is not included in the price of the apartment and is equal to 3.50€ / night per person (for children under 10 years is free). It will be collected in cash upon arrival. We check-in 24h-24h to facilitate business travelers or for those who have their own flight arrival times at night. For this reason, check-in after 20pm hours are charged with a small fee, please check this at time of booking.
transit: The area is well served by public transports, and buses that lead directly in the historic center pass right in front of the house on Viale Vaticano! If you do not like walking to get to the Metro we recommend buying the Rome Pass which includes all public transports, instead of the daily Metro ticket, so you can use all transports, including buses. To reach St. Peter's Basilica it is a 10 minute walk; simply walk along the Vatican Walls and you are there! To reach the Spanish Steps you can take the Metro A (red line) for 4 stops from Cipro, getting off at Piazza di Spagna station. Alternatively, the bus 49 passing on Viale Vaticano, therefore near the easier entrance of the flat, takes you in 10 minutes to Piazza Cavour; from there you can reach the Historical Center of Rome in 5 minutes walk, crossing Ponte Cavour (Via Tomacelli, Via del Corso, Via Condotti and Piazza di Spagna). To reach the Colosseum, always taking the Metro from Cipro (red line) you first arrive at Termini and cha
access: Our clients will be very welcome using common spaces, including kitchen, always having regard of any other guest present in the structure!
interaction: We will always be available and at complete disposal to give you all the help and assistance during the stay. We will welcome you at home by providing all the information on the best places to visit in Rome, as well as local cafes, restaurants and Roman trattorias, ice cream and pastry shops, as well public utilities stores such as supermarkets, pharmacies and household items!

In caso di ritardo non comunicato tempestivamente (almeno con 2 ore di anticipo) e oltre un tempo minimo di tolleranza di 30 minuti, il check-in potrebbe subire variazioni o nei casi peggiori (oltre l'ora di ritardo e in orari serali) si applicherá un costo supplementare di 10€ per ogni ora di ritardo. - City Tax non inclusa nel soggiorno pari a 3.50€ al giorno a persona in contanti all'arrivo (esclusi bambini fino a 10 anni). - Per arrivi oltre le ore 20pm verrá richiesto un supplemento, si prega di verificare l'importo in fase di prenotazione. - Per soggiorni superiori a 7gg verrá richiesto un supplemento di 5€ ad ospite (a settimana) per coprire i cambi di biancheria. Eventuale pulizia extra sará a carico dell'ospite. - Le buone regole che ognuno ha in cas
host_about:
Questo Appartamento é di Sem e Lucia! 

Sem, Tunisino di nascita, 25 anni fa ha deciso di venire in Italia..é da 14 anni che vive in Sicilia, una terra meravigliosa , piú precisamente a Trapani dove ha trovato l'amore della sua vita e dove ha costruito una famiglia stupenda.
Quello che non puó mancare nella sua vita sono il mare, il buon cibo, il buon vino e l'attività fisica in palestra!

No Pets, No smoking No extra persons

name: Cozy loft close to Colosseum and Central Station
summary: A just renovated indipendent loft in a very central area, 15 minutes from Colosseum and Central Train Station, well linked to the airports, metro at few metres. Full equipped with everything that you need for your stay, including a kitchen to prepare your meals. In an elegant and safe area, in a classy building, very peaceful and quiet. Close to the vibrant etnic area of the city and the main monuments, handy metro to go to Vatican in few minutes. Free & fast wi-fi internet 50 Mb/s!
space: Enjoy the eternal city in a just renovated and indipendent loft in a very central area of Rome! By walk you can reach the Colosseum and the Central Train Station in only 15 minutes. The metro/underground is a few metres away! From the airports there are buses and trains that stop in the Central Train Station that is very close. The loft is equipped with everything that you need for your confortable stay. There is a useful kitchen to prepare your own meals if you want, with all the equipments. The area is very elegant, the building is very classy and inside the loft is very quiet and peaceful, facing an internal garden. At a walking short distance there are the main monuments, like Colosseum, San Giovanni church, Santa Maria Maggiore Church and many others. The metro is at few metres and with it you can reach the historical center and the Vatican in few minutes. In the loft there is free and very fast (50 Mb/s) wi-fi internet, a computer is provided, and there is also a 22 inches monito

neighborhood_overview: The area is very close to the center, you can easily walk to the archeological area (Colosseo, Roman Forum, Circo Massimo, Caracalla baths). It is also very close to two of the mains churches of Rome, San Giovanni and Santa Maria Maggiore. With the metro you can reach the Vatican and San Peter in a few minutes. There are many shops and restaurants around, and a vibrant ethnic area at a short distance. Not far there is a nice and safe park where you can relax.
notes: We don't charge cleaning expenses to let you pay less money, but please clean to the best the house after your staying!
transit: The metro is a few metres away. There is a tram that goes to the Colosseum that is at 15 minutes walking distance. To came and go to the airports, you can reach Termini Station (2 metro stops or 15 minutes walking) and there there are trains and buses to reach them.
access: You can use a full equipped kitchen (fridge, gas cooker, electric oven, microwave, toaster, kettle, coffee eletric machine, etc) when you can cook your meals. You can eat in the living room in the nice round table. There is also a high chair for the babies! There is unlimited fast (50 Mb/s) wi-fi access to the internet in the house! There is a 22 inches monitor to watch online tv and movies. The use of  washing machine is €5 for each use. Check-in is after 4 p.m., check out is before 12 a.m., please respect these times. Normally I cannot change these times because I have guests before you and after you. For pratical reasons it's not possible to leave your luggage before the check-in or after the check-out. In the very close Termini station there is a depot for luggage. If you want to be sure to be able to do an early check-in or a late check-out simply book another nights before or after your stay! ;-) Of course we will have to agree for the check-in time as soon as possibile and anywa
interaction: With pleasure we will meet at the check in, I will give you a free map of Roma, I will show you the house, let you sign a contract  for the staying (necessary for italian law) and ask you for your personal data because I have to send them to the italian government. If you would like to interact more, I will be glad to know you better, do something together and maybe make friendship ! :-)
house_rules: The house is strictly no smoking! Take off your shoes in the flat. Don't break anything! Don't open the front door to anyone that you don't know. Check-in is after 4 p.m., check out is before 12 a.m.  Don't be too noisy for the neighbours, especially at night. Don't lose the keys. Clean the house after your staying to avoid to charge you more. Have fun! :-D ********* Vietato fumare in casa! Togli le scarpe nell'appartamento. Non rompere niente! Non aprire la porta di casa ad estranei. Il check-in è dalle 16, il check-out è entro le 12. Non disturbare i vicini, specialmente di notte. Non perdere le chiavi. Pulisci la casa dopo il tuo soggiorno per evitare ulteriori spese. Divertiti! :-D
host_about:
My name is Alfredo, I was born in Rome and I always lived here. 
I'm a normal guy that doesn't accept to be normal, so very soon I make a mess in my life. 
I am open minded and very curios, I can be very shy and people say that I look very gentle and peaceful. 
I try to always see things from another point of view, but I can be also very lazy in doing real stuff. 
I have a lot of interests but I am also dispersive. 
I can be very simple and very complicated: I have lot of contradictions and doubts! :-)
I am antifascist, antiraxist, antisexist and antispecist. 
I think everyone must be free and alive so I don't eat animal and I don't eat or use anything that comes from animals: someone would say I am vegan. :-) 
I like to read, photography, to spend time on computers, to cook, to eat, to drink, to meet strange people, to love, to relax on the beach, to trekking on mountains, animals, to walk. 

******************
Mi chiamo Alfredo, sono nato a Roma e sempre vissuto qui.
Sono un ragazzo normale a cui non piace la normalità, quindi spesso faccio un casino nella vita.
Sono di mentalità aperta e molto curioso, posso essere molto timido e dicono che sembro molto gentile e pacioso.
Cerco sempre di vedere le cose da un altro punto di vista, ma posso anche essere molto pigro nell'attivarmi.
Ho molti interessi ma sono anche dispersivo.
Posso essere molto semplice e molto complicato: ho un sacco di contraddizioni e dubbi! :-)
Sono antifascista, antirazzista, antisessista e antispecista.
Penso che tutti debbano essere liberi e vivi quindi non mangio animali e non mangio o uso niente che viene dagli animali: qualcuno potrebbe dire che sono vegano. :-)
Mi piace leggere, la fotografia, perdere tempo al pc, cucinare, mangiare, bere, incontrare persone strane, amare, rilassarmi sulla spiaggia, fare trekking in montagna, gli animali, viaggiare.

name: Cosy Plaza Mayor apartment in central Madrid
space: Cosy renovated apartment centrally located metres off famous Historic Centre & Plaza Mayor. Here you will be in the centre of all that Madrid has to offer. Walking distance to shops, river manzanares, Atocha Station, Retiro, Museums - Prado, Reina Sofia.... best tapas bars and ambience around. Enjoy fantastic musicians on your very doorstep. Great position. 5th floor apartment, no lift, renovated, appliances/ammenities. You'll be sleeping in a single bedsit area leading from lounge room. Window with fantastic views overlooking rooftops and lovely cathedral down the road. Apartment has supermarkets and markets with fresh produce, within 2 minutes walking distance. Famous Market San Miguel one of many markets to mention. Fast WIFI throughout apartment. Excellent transport; Metro and RENFE train in Sol, Buses and Taxis all within 5 minutes walk. From airport you can take renfe train direct to sol, apartment 5 minutes walk from here. You will be sharing apartment with a university student.

Walking distance to shops, river manzanares, Atocha Station, Retiro, Museums - Prado, Reina Sofia.... best tapas bars and ambience around. Enjoy fantastic musicians on your very doorstep. Famous Market San Miguel one of many markets to mention. Fast WIFI throughout apartment. Excellent transport; Metro and RENFE train in Sol, Buses and Taxis all within 5 minutes walk. From airport you can take renfe train direct to sol, apartment 5 minutes walk from here. You will be sharing apartment with a university student.
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is centrally located which makes it easy to access the supermarket( 3 mins away), train station Atocha (by foot 10mins), Plaza Mayor (just down stairs and you´re already there ;-), the royal palace, plaza de sol and the opera house by foot only 10 mins walking. Also the Thyssen, Prado and Reina Sofia museums are between 15-20 min walking. Not to mention you are in the heart of a shopping district Sol, Chueca, Serrano..The district is city life but if you walk only a few steps south you will enter the district of La Latina where the grand Sunday market is held "The Rastro", there is also a Sunday market held within the Plaza Mayor square.
transit: Alway´s best to walk around the city as the metro can take some time to move around especially with delays. However if you would like to visit the Train market in Embajadores you may need to catch transport not to get lost. The metro is close by 5 mins walking and there are 3 different lines you can catch La Latina, Sol (metro & cercanias, which is the fast train) and Opera, they are the 3 closest metros to the apartment. Atocha train station is only a short walk 10-15mins and there is an Airport transfer bus that stops in all terminals and is fairly direct.

host_about:
ENGLISH
Hello!

We are Maria and Caterina, direct owners of Ca Na Servera. 

We are two sisters that live and work in Mallorca. Maria has a PhD in Enviromental Microbiology and is a professor, and I (Caterina) am a Cardiologist in Hospital Universitari Son Espases.  We are really hardworking, but we like enjoying little pleasures that life offers, such as travelling, tasting different culture gastronomy, doing sport (mainly road cycling, that is one of the most touristic attraction of Mallorca), reading (that is a thing that my sister loves), etc. Nevertheless,  one of our most pleasures is the fact that we have the opportunity to live in an island like Mallorca, which has a huge diversity of landscapes and a big quantity of different activities to do!

He have been travelling a lot (Berlin, Stuttgart, Prague, Paris, Rome, London, Edinburgh, Tunisia, Mexico, Vietnam, etc.) and we have experimented many situations (good ones and not so good ones) that helped us to know what is important for a traveller. It is for that reason that if you are thinking about being our guest, we will try to help you in whatever you need and try you to have an enjoying stay in Ca Na Servera. 

An essential thing for a traveller is to find a place where he/she could rest and feel like home after spending a long day visiting different places. That is what we would like for us and, hence, what we would try to achive for you.

And more or less, this is our “travel philosophy”!!

DEUTSCH
Hallo !!

Wir sind Maria und Caterina Mas, direkten Besitzer von Ca Na Servera.

Wir sind zwei Schwestern, die auf Mallorca leben und arbeiten. Mary ist PhD in Umweltmikrobiologie und arbeitet als Lehrer, während ich (Caterina) bin Kardiologe in Mallorca Empfehlungskrankenhaus, Krankenhaus Universitari Son Espases. An zwei lieben wir arbeiten hart, sondern genießen auch die kleinen Freuden, die das Leben bietet uns, wie Reisen, versuchen, die Küche der verschiedenen Kulturen, Sport (insbesondere Rennrad, die auch touristische Attraktionen einer der wichtigsten ist Mallorca), lesen (das ist etwas, das meine Schwester, liebt Bücher von Intrigen und science Fiction), usw. Dennoch ist eine unserer größten Vergnügen die Tatsache, in einer Insel wie Mallorca zu leben, weil es eine Menge landschaftliche Vielfalt und Fülle von Aktivitäten präsentiert zu tun.

Mallorca bietet Ruhe, wenn gewünscht, oder mehr Bewegung, wenn der entgegengesetzte Fall; Strand oder in den Bergen; gutes Essen und Trinken ... Für uns wir lieben Orte auf der Insel zu helfen, und empfehlen, die unsere Gäste wünschen, entsprechend den Präferenzen der einzelnen. Und es ist niemand besser dafür als zwei einheimische junge Mädchen von Mallorca!

Wir haben ziemlich unterwegs (Berlin, Stuttgart, Prag, Paris, Rom, London, Edinburgh, Tunesien, Mexiko, Vietnam, etc.) und haben alle Arten von Situationen (gut und nicht so gut) erlebt, dass uns geholfen haben, wissen, was ist wichtig für einen Reisenden. Deshalb, wenn Sie denken, unser Gast sein, werden wir versuchen, Ihren Aufenthalt so angenehm wie möglich und helfen, so viel wie möglich zu machen!

Das Wesentliche für einen Reisenden ist es, einen Ort zu finden, und wie zu Hause fühlen, um sich nach einem langen Tag zu verbringen Dinge, ohne zu stoppen Besuch. Dies ist, was wir uns finden würden und deshalb werden wir versuchen zu bieten!

Und mehr oder weniger das ist unsere "Reise-Philosophie" !!


ESPAÑOL

Hola!! 

Somos María y Caterina Mas, propietarias directas de Ca Na Servera. 

Somos dos hermanas que viven y trabajan en Mallorca. María es Doctorada en Microbiología Ambiental y trabaja como profesora, mientras que yo (Caterina) soy Cardióloga en el hospital de referencia de Mallorca, Hospital Universitari Son Espases. A las dos nos encanta trabajar duro, pero también disfrutar de los pequeños placeres que nos ofrece la vida, como viajar, probar la gastronomía de diferentes culturas, hacer deporte (sobre todo bici de carretera, que además es uno de los  grandes atractivos turísticos de Mallorca), leer (eso es algo más de mi hermana, le encantan los libros de intriga y de ciencia ficción), etc. Aún así, uno de nuestros mayores placeres es el hecho de estar viviendo en una isla como Mallorca, ya que presenta mucha diversidad paisajística y gran cantidad de actividades por hacer. 

Mallorca ofrece tranquilidad si se desea, o más movimiento si es el caso contrario; playa o montaña; buena comida y bebida... A nosotras nos encanta poder ayudar y recomendar lugares de la isla que pudieran gustar a nuestro huéspedes, según las preferencias de cada uno. Y no hay nadie mejor para ello que dos chicas jóvenes autóctonas de Mallorca!

Hemos estado viajando bastante (Berlín, Stuttgart, Praga, París, Roma, Londres, Edimburgo, Túnez, Méjico, Vietnam, etc.) y hemos experimentado todo tipo de situaciones (buenas y no tan buenas) que nos han ayudado a saber qué es importante para un viajero. Es por eso que si te planteas ser nuestro huésped, intentaremos que tu estancia sea lo más placentera posible y ayudarte en todo lo posible!

Lo esencial para un viajero es encontrar un lugar donde poder descansar y sentirse como en casa después de pasar un largo día visitando cosas sin parar. Esto es lo que a nosotras nos gustaría encontrar y que, por tanto, vamos a intentar ofrecer!

Y más o menos ésta es nuestra "filosofía de viaje"!!

neighborhood_overview: I love our location. It's very central but quiet and so close to everything. Located between King's Cross St Pancras stations, the best connected stations in London, and the lovely leafy Barnsbury/Angel neighbourhood.  To the West, King's Cross' new development has an abundance of amenities that are along the walk from the station to our flat. Restaurants, supermarkets, bars, gyms, cafes, yoga studios, galleries, parks, stores and more. To the East is the lovely leafy traditional London neighbourhood of  Barnsbury with beautiful local gastro pubs around the corner (see photos) as well as a lot of restaurants, bars and shopping in Angel. Also being next to the canal (take a lovely stroll or grab a nearby bike share) and around the corner from an Overground station (part of tube system) makes for easy access to the best of all of London's transport options.
transit: ................. CANAL (WALKING / BICYCLE)  You can cross all of London walking/cycling along the Regents Canal. There are many pubs, restaurants, parks and even the Zoo along the canal. The canal is only 5 min walk from our place.  Walking westward along the canal you will find: Granary Square (lively pubs, food + parks along canal) Camden Market (fun lively area with affordable food + shopping) Regents Park / London Zoo (beautifully landscaped / pride of London) Little Venice (cute narrowboats / leafy towpaths) Walking eastward (from Angel) along the canal you will find: Haggerston "Riviera" (bars/restaurants along canal) Broadway Market (Saturdays - best market in London me thinks) Columbia Rd Flower Market (Sundays - lively & cute) Victoria Park (voted best park of UK - very bike friendly) Hackney Wick (trendy industrial area with bars along canal) There is a bike sharing station around the corner from our place and places to drop off near all above sights.  ................. TUBE
access: Along with their room, guests have access to the shared toilet and bathroom as well as the laundry room downstairs. I work in the living room / kitchen so we generally keep that door closed, more for keeping any noise and mess we make contained!
interaction: I work at home and so am generally around. If the door to the living room is closed please feel free to knock if you have any questions or just want to say hello! :)
house_rules: Please remove shoes downstairs. No guests.

INTERESTS

THINGS I CAN'T LIVE WITHOUT
- Books

FAVORITE TRAVEL EXPERIENCES

neighborhood_overview: The LOCATION: Roslindale is a safe and diverse Boston neighborhood located between Jamaica Plain and West Roxbury. This apartment is on Ardale Street, a quiet side street off Centre Street.  This is about one-half mile from Faulkner Hospital, walking distance to the renowned Arnold Arboretum park (look for it on (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN)), and about 20-minute drive to the Longwood Medical Center area. I have easy, restriction-free, on-street parking here, and a back yard. Just one block from the house, there is a 7-11 convenience store, a dry-cleaner, a Mexican restaurant, a pizza parlor, a popular sports bar and grill (similar to an Irish Pub), and another restaurant for breakfast and lunch.  The house is located 1/2 mile from Roslindale Square where you will find more restaurants, 4 bakeries, the public library and the post office. There is a superb farmers market here every Saturday. The fast-train to downtown Boston stops there, too.
notes: I am in a scenic part of Boston with a couple big parks nearby, and Jamaica Pond, where you can rent a sail boat or jog the paved perimeter path, within a mile away. Here is a clue to my personality:  Favorite singers are Judy Collins, Ari Hest, Miguel Bose and the British rock band, James. My top favorite places to travel to are Oaxaca, Mexico and Budapest, Hungary. In years gone by, I have had repeated trips to Paris and to Tunisia, also. These days I am mostly home, spending a lot of time in front of my iMac, writing copy, filling orders or coding for websites.
transit: PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION: From the house, quick public transportation to Forest Hills station (Orange Line and Commuter Rail) is via two nearby MBTA bus lines. The #38 bus stops one-half block away, and takes you past the Faulkner, then to Jamaica Plain and Forest Hills.  The #51 bus stops one block away, and goes a more direct route to Forest Hills. (The bus also goes to Cleveland Circle in Brookline.) Between the two bus lines, there is a bus that stops here every 15 minutes or so on weekdays; but no service on Sunday. ALSO, the apartment is just 1/2 mile walk to the Roslindale Village MBTA commuter rail stop, Needham Line. The train takes you to Ruggles Station at Northeastern Univ., to Back Bay station and to South Station in downtown Boston, in about 15 minutes time.  There are more city busses, running 7 days a week, from this MBTA rail station. You can also pick up ZIP Cars there.  GETTING HERE FROM LOGAN AIRPORT: By public transportation: You take the free shuttle bus at the airpo
access: I am living in the apartment during your stay, and I work from home, so I'm there most of the time.  Guests are welcome to use the kitchen and all cooking utensils, refrigerator, etc. I have a gas stove, toaster oven, microwave, convection oven and a pressure cooker! I have a backyard garden, so if you are here during August and September, be prepared for tomatoes and cucumbers! In addition to your personal room, you can also use the living room which includes a 32-inch HDTV with an Apple TV connection.  The bathroom, adjacent to your room, is shared.  The only room that is off limits is my bedroom on the opposite side of the apartment. I have a clothes washer and dryer in the basement for your use.
interaction: ABOUT ME: I'm a laid-back, friendly, unmarried guy. I work from home, spending a lot of time on the computer. I have an website that sells handmade things from Mexico. It is called "Viva Oaxaca Folk Art." You will see lots of folk art in the apartment. I also run websites for other small companies. I don’t smoke, don’t have overnight guests. I keep regular hours, am friendly, considerate and quiet. I am one of the original Boston AIRBNB hosts, having signed-up with them in 2008.   I am a big traveler myself, and I love hearing stories of where guests have been or where they are heading to next.
house_rules: I encourage you to use my kitchen, cooking and laundry facilities. There is no additional charge to use the washer/dryer in the basement.  No smoking, inside or outside. Come home as late as you want.  If you come home stumbling drunk, it's OK the first time. If you do it again, and you wake up me or the neighbors downstairs, we will be annoyed.  (Just so you know . . . )
host_about:
I am a middle-aged, single male with a wide range of interests and creative outlets.  I have traveled frequently, in much of the world, especially central Europe, including Hungary and Slovakia. In recent years I have had many trips to Mexico, where I buy folk art for my online business, called Viva Oaxaca Folk Art. I love meeting new people, especially travelers with stories to tell.  

In addition to the above, I run web sites for small companies, including a physical therapy practice, a cancer treatment center and a colonial era historic house and museum. 

In the 1980s, I was a publicist and concert producer, and have presented many concerts with Judy Collins, as well as with Ella Fitzgerald, Laura Nyro, Tom Rush, Barbara Cook and Karen Akers. Now I run a channel on YouTube called "beta.hifi.archive" that is a collection of 50 years of video clips from the career of Judy Collins. 

So come to Boston, and stay with me. Enjoy some tomatoes and cucumbers from my garden, explore my world of Mexican folk art, and let's talk about our travel adventures.

host_about:
ENGLISH
Hello!

We are Maria and Caterina, direct owners of Ca Na Servera. 

We are two sisters that live and work in Mallorca. Maria has a PhD in Enviromental Microbiology and is a professor, and I (Caterina) am a Cardiologist in Hospital Universitari Son Espases.  We are really hardworking, but we like enjoying little pleasures that life offers, such as travelling, tasting different culture gastronomy, doing sport (mainly road cycling, that is one of the most touristic attraction of Mallorca), reading (that is a thing that my sister loves), etc. Nevertheless,  one of our most pleasures is the fact that we have the opportunity to live in an island like Mallorca, which has a huge diversity of landscapes and a big quantity of different activities to do!

He have been travelling a lot (Berlin, Stuttgart, Prague, Paris, Rome, London, Edinburgh, Tunisia, Mexico, Vietnam, etc.) and we have experimented many situations (good ones and not so good ones) that helped us to know what is important for a traveller. It is for that reason that if you are thinking about being our guest, we will try to help you in whatever you need and try you to have an enjoying stay in Ca Na Servera. 

An essential thing for a traveller is to find a place where he/she could rest and feel like home after spending a long day visiting different places. That is what we would like for us and, hence, what we would try to achive for you.

And more or less, this is our “travel philosophy”!!

DEUTSCH
Hallo !!

Wir sind Maria und Caterina Mas, direkten Besitzer von Ca Na Servera.

Wir sind zwei Schwestern, die auf Mallorca leben und arbeiten. Mary ist PhD in Umweltmikrobiologie und arbeitet als Lehrer, während ich (Caterina) bin Kardiologe in Mallorca Empfehlungskrankenhaus, Krankenhaus Universitari Son Espases. An zwei lieben wir arbeiten hart, sondern genießen auch die kleinen Freuden, die das Leben bietet uns, wie Reisen, versuchen, die Küche der verschiedenen Kulturen, Sport (insbesondere Rennrad, die auch touristische Attraktionen einer der wichtigsten ist Mallorca), lesen (das ist etwas, das meine Schwester, liebt Bücher von Intrigen und science Fiction), usw. Dennoch ist eine unserer größten Vergnügen die Tatsache, in einer Insel wie Mallorca zu leben, weil es eine Menge landschaftliche Vielfalt und Fülle von Aktivitäten präsentiert zu tun.

Mallorca bietet Ruhe, wenn gewünscht, oder mehr Bewegung, wenn der entgegengesetzte Fall; Strand oder in den Bergen; gutes Essen und Trinken ... Für uns wir lieben Orte auf der Insel zu helfen, und empfehlen, die unsere Gäste wünschen, entsprechend den Präferenzen der einzelnen. Und es ist niemand besser dafür als zwei einheimische junge Mädchen von Mallorca!

Wir haben ziemlich unterwegs (Berlin, Stuttgart, Prag, Paris, Rom, London, Edinburgh, Tunesien, Mexiko, Vietnam, etc.) und haben alle Arten von Situationen (gut und nicht so gut) erlebt, dass uns geholfen haben, wissen, was ist wichtig für einen Reisenden. Deshalb, wenn Sie denken, unser Gast sein, werden wir versuchen, Ihren Aufenthalt so angenehm wie möglich und helfen, so viel wie möglich zu machen!

Das Wesentliche für einen Reisenden ist es, einen Ort zu finden, und wie zu Hause fühlen, um sich nach einem langen Tag zu verbringen Dinge, ohne zu stoppen Besuch. Dies ist, was wir uns finden würden und deshalb werden wir versuchen zu bieten!

Und mehr oder weniger das ist unsere "Reise-Philosophie" !!


ESPAÑOL

Hola!! 

Somos María y Caterina Mas, propietarias directas de Ca Na Servera. 

Somos dos hermanas que viven y trabajan en Mallorca. María es Doctorada en Microbiología Ambiental y trabaja como profesora, mientras que yo (Caterina) soy Cardióloga en el hospital de referencia de Mallorca, Hospital Universitari Son Espases. A las dos nos encanta trabajar duro, pero también disfrutar de los pequeños placeres que nos ofrece la vida, como viajar, probar la gastronomía de diferentes culturas, hacer deporte (sobre todo bici de carretera, que además es uno de los  grandes atractivos turísticos de Mallorca), leer (eso es algo más de mi hermana, le encantan los libros de intriga y de ciencia ficción), etc. Aún así, uno de nuestros mayores placeres es el hecho de estar viviendo en una isla como Mallorca, ya que presenta mucha diversidad paisajística y gran cantidad de actividades por hacer. 

Mallorca ofrece tranquilidad si se desea, o más movimiento si es el caso contrario; playa o montaña; buena comida y bebida... A nosotras nos encanta poder ayudar y recomendar lugares de la isla que pudieran gustar a nuestro huéspedes, según las preferencias de cada uno. Y no hay nadie mejor para ello que dos chicas jóvenes autóctonas de Mallorca!

Hemos estado viajando bastante (Berlín, Stuttgart, Praga, París, Roma, Londres, Edimburgo, Túnez, Méjico, Vietnam, etc.) y hemos experimentado todo tipo de situaciones (buenas y no tan buenas) que nos han ayudado a saber qué es importante para un viajero. Es por eso que si te planteas ser nuestro huésped, intentaremos que tu estancia sea lo más placentera posible y ayudarte en todo lo posible!

Lo esencial para un viajero es encontrar un lugar donde poder descansar y sentirse como en casa después de pasar un largo día visitando cosas sin parar. Esto es lo que a nosotras nos gustaría encontrar y que, por tanto, vamos a intentar ofrecer!

Y más o menos ésta es nuestra "filosofía de viaje"!!

space: There is one double bedroom with a seperate living room and kitchen.  All newly refurbished. There is a double sofa bed in the living room so can accomodate 4 for a short stay.  We have a smart TV with freeview and unlimited broadband wifi.  You will also have fresh bath towels, hand towels, shampoo, conditioner, hair dryer, iron, ironing board, hangers. Kitchen is fully equipped with all cooking equipment, dishwasher and washing machine.

neighborhood_overview: The road that the apartment is on is amazingly quiet considering it is so central. It is what people comment on most. There is great access to public transport as well as easy walks to the river, Holland Park or full on shopping. There are plenty of restaurants, takeaways and 24 hour shops locally and it's easy to be a full on tourist or live like a Londoner. From Gucci to Street market it's all in the doorstep.
transit: Short walking distance to Picadilly, Central, district and Hammersmith and City underground lines as well as London Overground and a plethora of bus routes.  Direct routes to Gatwick, Heathrow and even Brighton.
access: The whole apartment is available for you to enjoy.
interaction: We live about 20 minutes away so not on the doorstep but always available if you need any help.
host_about:
Hi, we are Shahram and Rachael Sadegh, married for way too long with two young daughters.  Rachael is British and Shahram is Iranian and speaks Farsi and Turkish. We have lived in London since 2004 and definitely think West is best. We are very easy going and after experiencing airbnb hosts ourselves thought we would try being hosts. We're just learning how to travel with small children which gives us a whole new appreciation for how much travelling needs differ between people.  We'd like to think we're considerate guests and friendly accommodating (though not interfering) hosts.

Rachael works in local government and Shahram designs chandeliers and we both love discovering new places, home or away (though our recent trip to Tunisia was a bit hairy!)
street: Sinclair Road, London, England W14 0NL, United Kingdom

name: ROOM 4. BED&BREAKFAST CASPIAN HOTEL
summary: Room 4: 4 people. 1 double bed and 2 single beds.  With breakfast.  Minimum 2 nights.
description: Room 4: 4 people. 1 double bed and 2 single beds.  With breakfast.  Minimum 2 nights.
host_about:
In the heart of Ealing, known as Queen of suburbs, The Caspian offers cosy rooms with continental breakfast in a friendly family environment. We have been serving the local and international community for decades and the hospitality of The Caspian has not diminished over these years.


Caspian is conveniently nestled on the corner of Haven Green. Set in a Victorian Era house, all rooms are double glazed with TV, free WIFI and seating area provided. Some rooms have period features and large windows with garden view.

We offer a large variety of rooms: diversified by their size, colour and price.

We have onsite parking and a meeting room is available for hire. It offers a pleasant ambiance for board meetings or private reunions.





The Caspian is a 2 minutes’ walk from Ealing Broadway Station and 15 minutes from Central London. Ealing Broadway shopping centres, restaurants and all amenities are a short walk. Our sister La Baguette coffee shop/restaurant offers delicious Tunisian and international food (10% discount for Hotel guests). 

So much is going on in Ealing: Ealing Summer Festivals (Jazz, Blues, Comedy, Beer, Carnival) in July, Ealing Half Marathon in September.
 ...and around Ealing: Sport and Music events at Wembley Stadium all year, and the unique grand Westfield Shopping Malls is a short bus or train ride. The significant Walpole Park along with Pitzhanger Manor are a short stroll from Caspian.

Caspian Hotel is just 20 minutes’ drive from Heathrow Airport. The M4, M40 and A406 motorways are only 5 minutes’ drive.





The Caspian has been visited by top consultant Alex Polizzi from The Hotel Inspector TV Series on 3 consecutive years.
street: The Broadway, London, W5, United Kingdom

neighborhood_overview: Clapham has two main areas for evening entertainment; Clapham High Street and Clapham Junction. Clapham Junction boasts the famous Clapham Grand, a venue hosting a great variety of events depending on the night. Most tastes are catered for in the Grand at some time or other, and the place has a great feel to it. Inigo is a much smaller bar/club about five minutes from the station, and plays a wide range of funky house and dance music along with regular promotional drinks offers. Clapham Junction also has a Rileys' 24-hour pool bar, which is a bit of a boys club and hosts both pool and poker tournaments.
transit: Transportation Clapham Junction is about eight minutes from Waterloo, with 35 trains an hour. It's nice to have guaranteed timing in your journey to work! There are no Underground stations in Clapham Junction but with so many trains, it hardly seems to matter. The station also provides you with the opportunity for a day out almost anywhere in the south of England without too much hassle. The High Street has three stations on the Northern Line (Clapham South, North and Common), which can all have you in the West End or the city in fifteen minutes . Clapham High Street, a small usually unmanned station, also has a service to Victoria. The area also has regular night buses from central London; so you'll never have to leave your drink/pull/friends to go and catch that irritatingly full last train home.

name: Charming cosy apartment in Paris 16
space: My apartment is located in the 16th district (west Paris) in a residential quiet area.  You'll be charmed by the lovely paved yard (classified as a historical patrimony of the city).  Not far from the Eiffel Tower and the Bois de Boulogne, the apartment is close to the Seine. You can access to lots of different activities.  The closest Metro station is Porte de Saint Cloud (line 9) and you can easily find taxi and bus close by. It is composed of one bedroom, a living room, a kitchen, a bathroom (with toilets separated). Tv, internet and a washing machine are available. It really is a cosy place to enjoy your holidays in Paris, and you'll surely enjoy the bed after a hard day of sightseeing !  The apartment is furnished with comfy yet beautiful furniture. An old-fashioned door, a brick stone wall, a kitchen opened on the living room, vintage tables :  i'm sure you'll like the cachet of it !

host_about:
Hello there
I've been living in the "Paris area" my whole life so far. This is quite an exciting city and there's a lot to do around the capital as well.
I love traveling and discovering other countries. I try to do it as often as i can afford. So far I've been to Kenya, Thailand, the United States, Turky, Marrocco, Tunisia and of course to a few countries of western Europe (my neighbours ! Italy, Belgium, Spain, England, Ireland).
I've got a lot see and i hope I'll be on a plane really soon !
My other passion is cinema : i watch a lot of movies on dvds, at the theatres, i read magazines, write on a blog, etc...a real cinema buff !
When I travel, I prefer renting a place to stay rather than going to a hotel : it's cheaper for one if you want to take the time to discover a city, and it's cosier as well : you can feel "at home" whereas you're abroad, it makes the experience the more appreciable. 
Hope you'll enjoy your stay in Paris !!

host_about:
Hello, I am  Petya Hottz. 
Welcome to my great international family in New York. Let me show you around.
I live in a 3 bedroom apartment in Astoria, Queens, with my husband Thiago, who is from Brazil and a Chinese boy Jack. I have a lot of great locations and  of course they are not in the same apartment. Most are in Astoria around us, Woodside, Jackson Heights and  MANHATTAN.  All locations are very nice, clean, well experienced hosting people from all around the world, in pretty convenient and safe  neighborhoods. You are very welcome to be part of my little, international family. 
 I am originally from Bulgaria and I speak English, Bulgarian, Russian, and a little bit of French. I am a very friendly positive person and I am also very open to foreign cultures, music, food, and customs. New York is a very unique city because people are from all around the world and contribute to the diversity of daily living.
As a professional figure skater I have participated in competitions throughout most of Europe. As a child I traveled often with my family to France, Germany, Italy, California, Tunisia and Spain. In addition, I have traveled extensively to North America, Brazil. I love to engage in sports, yoga, tennis, skating, skiing, swimming, hiking, music, dancing and I love to cook. My father and my brother in law are professional chefs. I guess I inherited the passion from them to prepare delicious foods. I would love for you to experience my cuisine.
In addition about my rooms, they all are located in a great neighborhood with restaurants, bars, international food, stores, libraries, parks, schools, shopping malls, and cinemas. Everything is nearby and convenient to public transportation which runs 24 hours a days. It is only 5-25 min to NYC. Or if you need a taxi, they are abundantly available outside the (URL HIDDEN) location is located a block or a few blocks from  subway stations. All rooms are new furnished, AC, WiFi and Cable, all included in the price. I also can offer you occasional free skating classes with me at the local rink.
Welcome to my apartment. I know you are going to feel like you are home. I am waiting for you my new friend. Welcome to New York!

Montmartre cathedral is only 15 minutes’ walk so you will get the advantage of being close enough and live the real Parisian life. I can provide a full list of options for eating out. access: You will have the entire apartment for you. I am as flexible as I can be on arrival and departure but it is essential that visitors consult me on and keep to their plans.
interaction: You can contact me for any question you may have. I am travelling extensively for work and if I am not there when you arrive, a friend of mine will supply you with the key to the apartment.
host_about:
I am a young Italian working for an internet company. 

I was born in Italy, and lived most of my life between UK, Ireland, Mexico, Tunisia and Spain. I love traveling, cooking and photography.

I love the city where I live. There is so much going on - from fabulous theater, amazing art, wonderful brassiere, interesting lectures to just having a nice wine with friends. If you want any tips and tricks on what to do and where to go I'd love to try to help! :) 

When I travel I love comforts! Therefore, I'm particularly careful to make sure that my guests have an unforgettable stay!

I try to create a comfortable space that you can enjoy while exploring the city - and I'm always happy to give advice or do what I can to make your visit a better experience. If you have questions or would like to book, please send me an inquiry with your dates. I look forward to hearing from you!

Natsumi

Angelo. In the last century, it has become one of the most charming residential quarter of the capital, with many historical places and elegant buildings, Liberty style villas, boutiques, shops, restaurants, patisseries, coffee shops and cool night clubs where spending a pleasant and exciting time. name: vintage nice double room in Rome up to 4 people!
summary: A vintage and confortable double room (up to 4) to enjoy the experience of Italian life in a classic, big and full equipped flat in Rome, in a central and well connected area. Buses at 5 minutes, metro at 10 minutes, city trains at 15 minutes, walk to the Colosseum in less than 30 minutes. Night buses too! Easy to reach from airports. Very quiet, safe and not touristical area, full of not expensive bars, restaurants, shops. Very big and wonderful park at 5 minutes, with Roman ruins inside.
space: A nice and big double room in an original Italian vintage home that was my granparents'! Almost all the decorations and the furniture is original to feel back in the 60's! The beds are comfortable, the room is very quiet, overlooking on an internal courtyard. Your pets, if friendly, are welcome (ask me). IMPORTANT: the double bed is for 2 people, but in the room there is a bunk bed to host other 2 people with an extra of only €15 per night per person. VERY IMPORTANT:  If you are in 2 I will prepare the double bed for you. If you are 2 (or 3) but you still want to sleep in 2 (or 3) separated beds, one could sleep in the double bed and the other(s) in the bulk bed(s) for only €5 more per night (each) to be paid cash at the arrival. You have to tell me this preference before your arrival so I can prepare the beds. NOTE ABOUT HEATING: The heating is centralized from the building and because of municipality laws it can be on only from the 15th of November to 15th of Avril and only from 6AM

neighborhood_overview: I live in an area pretty close to the center! You can walk to the archeological area (Colosseo, Circo Massimo, Appia Antica, Caracalla bath, Aurelian walls). There are many shops and restaurants around. There is also a big park very close when you can relax!
notes: You can bring your pets, I will like to know them too! In the house there will be all you need for them. They should always be kept in your room, unless you book the two rooms of the house or you ask to the other guests.
transit: With a ten minutes walk you can reach the metro that takes you to the center and to Vatican-San Pietro. At few metres there are buses that go to the archeological and Renaissance center and to the main railways station. At 1.5 km there are city railway lines that go to Fiumicino Airport, to the beach, to Ostia Antica, to lake Bracciano, to Cerveteri's necropolis. I am very well linked to the place where you will arrive in Rome! To reach home from main railway station Termini there is A metro line (only 4 stops, 1 km from home) or a direct bus. To reach home from Fiumicino airport there is a train that stops a Roma Tuscolana (1,5 km from home), or another train that goes to Termini station and cheaper buses that goes to Termini station as well. To reach the house from Ciampino airport there are buses that reach the A metro line (Anagina stop) that brings to my home, or buses that goes to Termini station.
access: You can use a full equipped kitchen (fridge, gas cooker, electric oven, microwave, toaster, kettle, etc) when you can cook your meals and eat them! Or you can eat in the big dining room, where you can also relax or chat with the other guests. The bathroom is shared with the other guests  that can be other 3 people (unless you book the whole flat) so please consider this in using it (for timing and cleanliness). Please also don't take too long showers. While you are here, I will clean as often as I can the common area (because of italian law I cannot clean your room). There is unlimited wi-fi access to the internet in the house! The washing machine is €5 for each use. I will do it for you. I cannot include breakfast in my offer (always because of the italian law) but you can cook your own! Check-in is after 4 p.m., check out is before 12 a.m., please respect these times. Normally I cannot change these times because I have guests before you and after you, but maybe you could leave your l
interaction: With pleasure we will meet at the check in, I will give you a free map of Roma, I will show you the house, let you sign a contract  for the staying (necessary for italian law) and ask you for your details because I have to send them to the italian government. If you need to leave your luggage before check-in time you could do it from 12 PM, ask me in advance to be sure it will be possible. If you will need to leave your luggage for some hours after the check-out we have to agree how, ask me in advance to be sure it will be possibile. If you came late at night (after 8 PM) I will let you find the keys without me being there. I live in a very close house, so if you need some help you can call me with the house phone. If you would like to interact more, I will be glad to know you better, do something together and maybe make friendship ! :-)
house_rules: Don't break anything! Always close the windows when you exit. Don't open the front door to anyone that you don't know. Check-in is after 4 p.m., check out is before 12 a.m.  Don't be too noisy for the neighbours, especially at night. Don't spend too much time in the shared bathroom and save energy for the Earth. Don't lose the keys. Try to have fun! :-D
host_about:
My name is Alfredo, I was born in Rome and I always lived here. 
I'm a normal guy that doesn't accept to be normal, so very soon I make a mess in my life. 
I am open minded and very curios, I can be very shy and people say that I look very gentle and peaceful. 
I try to always see things from another point of view, but I can be also very lazy in doing real stuff. 
I have a lot of interests but I am also dispersive. 
I can be very simple and very complicated: I have lot of contradictions and doubts! :-)
I am antifascist, antiraxist, antisexist and antispecist. 
I think everyone must be free and alive so I don't eat animal and I don't eat or use anything that comes from animals: someone would say I am vegan. :-) 
I like to read, photography, to spend time on computers, to cook, to eat, to drink, to meet strange people, to love, to relax on the beach, to trekking on mountains, animals, to walk. 

******************
Mi chiamo Alfredo, sono nato a Roma e sempre vissuto qui.
Sono un ragazzo normale a cui non piace la normalità, quindi spesso faccio un casino nella vita.
Sono di mentalità aperta e molto curioso, posso essere molto timido e dicono che sembro molto gentile e pacioso.
Cerco sempre di vedere le cose da un altro punto di vista, ma posso anche essere molto pigro nell'attivarmi.
Ho molti interessi ma sono anche dispersivo.
Posso essere molto semplice e molto complicato: ho un sacco di contraddizioni e dubbi! :-)
Sono antifascista, antirazzista, antisessista e antispecista.
Penso che tutti debbano essere liberi e vivi quindi non mangio animali e non mangio o uso niente che viene dagli animali: qualcuno potrebbe dire che sono vegano. :-)
Mi piace leggere, la fotografia, perdere tempo al pc, cucinare, mangiare, bere, incontrare persone strane, amare, rilassarmi sulla spiaggia, fare trekking in montagna, gli animali, viaggiare.

neighborhood_overview: If there's any area of San Francisco that evokes images of the long-gone '60s hippie culture, the Haight is it. Fragments of that flower-power, incense-burning, acid-dropping, tie-dye-wearing, peace-and-love-vibing era can be purchased at smoke shops and Eastern-influenced outlets bearing names like Dreams of Kathmandu and The Love of Ganesha. But save for a few hippie relics, the Haight today is a whole new scene. Exclusive boutiques, high-end vintage-clothing shops, second-hand stores, Internet cafés and hip restaurants have all settled in, making the Haight one of San Francisco's commercial centers.

neighborhood_overview: The house is located on a tree line street, all private houses. The subway 7 train line is 3 blocks away from the house and it takes about 15 minutes to be in Times Square. The cost of a single ride ticket is 2.75 and the cost of the unlimited ride ticket for 1 week is 31. The 7 train runs 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. A taxi ride to Manhattan will take you about 15 minutes and about 18 dollars at the most. Sunnyside is a diverse neighborhood with people from different ethnic backgrounds, Europeans, Japanese, Irish, Koreans, Indians, Nepalis, Tibetans and Spanish. A lot of the professionals working in major companies in Wall street and Manhattan live in Sunnyside. Due to the diversity you have no shortage of restaurants and bars in this neighborhood. One of the best Japanese, Korean, Thai, Turkish, Spanish, Chinese, Vietnamese, Indian, Nepal/ Tibetan can all be found with 3 blocks of the house. There are also cafe shops and chain fast food in Sunnyside: Starbucks, Caffe Bene, Dunkin
transit: 7 Train line is 3 blocks away from the house which runs 24/7 and it takes 15 minutes to be in Times Square center of Manhattan. Taxi ride to the city are also cheap and affordable. From JFK the taxi ride to the house is 35 minutes and costs about 40 dollars and from Laguardia Airport the house is about 20 minutes and costs about 18 dollars.  From JFK, there is an Airtrain (5) that takes you to the subway station Sutphin Bvd in Jamaica and from there, you can take the E train line until 74th street- Jackson Heights and transfer to the 7 train line until 40th street station.

Please be courteous and treat the place like it is your own house. If you come back to the apartment at late hours please be reasonable and quiet. No Smoking inside the apartment  No Pets  No extra sleep over guest  Please keep it low after 10:30 PM (We don't want to have the neighbors complaining)  When checking out please throw the garbages in the bins in the front, close the door behind and leave the keys on the table.

Two professionals in New York City, myself, originally from Nepal and my fiancee, originally from France. We both love to travel, we love trying  different authentic cuisines and we like to learn about different cultures. host_location: New York, New York, United States
host_about:
Hello, I am  Petya Hottz. 
Welcome to my great international family in New York. Let me show you around.
I live in a 3 bedroom apartment in Astoria, Queens, with my husband Thiago, who is from Brazil and a Chinese boy Jack. I have a lot of great locations and  of course they are not in the same apartment. Most are in Astoria around us, Woodside, Jackson Heights and  MANHATTAN.  All locations are very nice, clean, well experienced hosting people from all around the world, in pretty convenient and safe  neighborhoods. You are very welcome to be part of my little, international family. 
 I am originally from Bulgaria and I speak English, Bulgarian, Russian, and a little bit of French. I am a very friendly positive person and I am also very open to foreign cultures, music, food, and customs. New York is a very unique city because people are from all around the world and contribute to the diversity of daily living.
As a professional figure skater I have participated in competitions throughout most of Europe. As a child I traveled often with my family to France, Germany, Italy, California, Tunisia and Spain. In addition, I have traveled extensively to North America, Brazil. I love to engage in sports, yoga, tennis, skating, skiing, swimming, hiking, music, dancing and I love to cook. My father and my brother in law are professional chefs. I guess I inherited the passion from them to prepare delicious foods. I would love for you to experience my cuisine.
In addition about my rooms, they all are located in a great neighborhood with restaurants, bars, international food, stores, libraries, parks, schools, shopping malls, and cinemas. Everything is nearby and convenient to public transportation which runs 24 hours a days. It is only 5-25 min to NYC. Or if you need a taxi, they are abundantly available outside the (URL HIDDEN) location is located a block or a few blocks from  subway stations. All rooms are new furnished, AC, WiFi and Cable, all included in the price. I also can offer you occasional free skating classes with me at the local rink.
Welcome to my apartment. I know you are going to feel like you are home. I am waiting for you my new friend. Welcome to New York!

space: Dear guest airbnb,  Studio to let right in the heart of Paris in the switched-on quarter of the 11th Arrondissement 2 minutes from Metro station.  Studio is not included in a flat. You will not have to share anything. Furnished room with built-in kitchenette, small bathroom with shower and toilets, television, electric heating. Unpretentious but with all the basics for a couple to spend a weekend in Paris at the minimum of expense.  The studio is in quiet surroundings on the second floor looking over a courtyard; without any noise pollution but with all the advantages of the trendy quarter of the Bastille in Paris. The shops stay open until 10 p.m. and there is no lack of cafés and places to go to right next to the bedsit. The studio is unpretentious but provides all that’s needed to spend a few nights at low prices - single or couple. The Metro station  is 2 minutes from the building. host_about:
As CEO and creator of the organic lingerie brand "Do you green" and educated as an architect DPLG (diplômé par le gouvernement – government qualified) I have enjoyed working and living abroad when I had the opportunity - in Taiwan and today in Tunisia, where I travel regularly. I am a fan of the television programme "J'irai dormir chez vous"* – (I don’t know if you know it?) I can give you tips for interesting visits and shopping addresses or my favourite restaurants in Paris – don’t hesitate to ask me.   The best cafés in Paris – in my opinion – are in the luxury hotels - and for a price that is astonishingly reasonable for the place and comfort (and you can stay there several hours). I recommend visiting one at least! I wish you to enjoy your visit and have a magnificent stay in this beautiful capital!

* J'irai dormir chez vous - Antoine de Maximin invites himself into ordinary people’s homes all over the world accompanied by just two cameras.

host_about:
Qui suis je ? une parisienne, une cinéphile, une grande voyageuse, une apprentie photographe... 
J'aime mon quartier, aller au ciné, partir en vacances très loin, mes amis, aller au resto, aller à la Gym, parler d'autres langues (même si ce n'est que quelques mots).
Je n'aime pas :  les chiens (ça fait peur !), quand les plantes meurent (ce qui m'arrive assez souvent hélas !)...
Mes voyages : USA, Canada, Thailande, Japon, Indonésie, Mexique, Maroc, Tunisie, Panama, Espagne, Portugal, Autriche, Allemagne...
Ceux à venir : Australie, Vietnam, Perou, Afrique du Sud...

Who am I : a Parisian, a cinephile, a traveller, a try-to-be photographer.
I like my neighborhood, going to the movie, going on vacation very far, my friends, go to restaurants, go to sports,  speaking foreign languages (even a few words...)
I don't like dogs (they scare me), dying plants (which happen often to me I must confess !)... 
Where I've been : USA, Canada, Thailande, Japon, Indonésie, Mexique, Maroc, Tunisie, Panama, Espagne, Portugal, Autriche, Allemagne...
Where I want to go : Australie, Vietnam, Perou, South Africa...
I hope you would like the city as much as I love it !

name: ROOM 8. BED&BREAKFAST CASPIAN HOTEL
summary: Room 8 ATTIC: 2 people.  2 single beds.  With breakfast. Minimum 2 nights.
description: Room 8 ATTIC: 2 people.  2 single beds.  With breakfast. Minimum 2 nights.
host_about:
In the heart of Ealing, known as Queen of suburbs, The Caspian offers cosy rooms with continental breakfast in a friendly family environment. We have been serving the local and international community for decades and the hospitality of The Caspian has not diminished over these years.


Caspian is conveniently nestled on the corner of Haven Green. Set in a Victorian Era house, all rooms are double glazed with TV, free WIFI and seating area provided. Some rooms have period features and large windows with garden view.

We offer a large variety of rooms: diversified by their size, colour and price.

We have onsite parking and a meeting room is available for hire. It offers a pleasant ambiance for board meetings or private reunions.





The Caspian is a 2 minutes’ walk from Ealing Broadway Station and 15 minutes from Central London. Ealing Broadway shopping centres, restaurants and all amenities are a short walk. Our sister La Baguette coffee shop/restaurant offers delicious Tunisian and international food (10% discount for Hotel guests). 

So much is going on in Ealing: Ealing Summer Festivals (Jazz, Blues, Comedy, Beer, Carnival) in July, Ealing Half Marathon in September.
 ...and around Ealing: Sport and Music events at Wembley Stadium all year, and the unique grand Westfield Shopping Malls is a short bus or train ride. The significant Walpole Park along with Pitzhanger Manor are a short stroll from Caspian.

Caspian Hotel is just 20 minutes’ drive from Heathrow Airport. The M4, M40 and A406 motorways are only 5 minutes’ drive.





The Caspian has been visited by top consultant Alex Polizzi from The Hotel Inspector TV Series on 3 consecutive years.
street: The Broadway, London, W5, United Kingdom

name: my veg double room for you in Rome!
summary: I offer you my living room to try the experience of real life in a real flat in Rome! I live with my animals in a central area of the city. You will have the warm of a real house with real Italian people, but to be confortable you should love animals
space: It's my living room! So don't expect a wardrobe or a b&b: it's a room of my house, and you will be my loved guest! The bed sofa is very confortable and the room pretty quiet. Sheets and blankets are provided. I will clean your room during your stay if you don't leave anything on the floor. VERY IMPORTANT: the sofa-bed is for 2 people but, if you are 3, in the same room there is a big couch so 1 of you 3 can sleep on the couch adding €10. IMPORTANT: I don't host children, because I have a playfull dog that get very excited with them and they normally don't know how to protect themself, and if they show fear it's also worst: sorry but I can't take the responsabilty for them.

neighborhood_overview: I live in an area pretty close to the center. You can walk to the archeological area (Colosseo, Circo Massimo, Appia Antica, Caracalla bath, Aurelian walls). There are many shops and restaurants around.
notes: My dog Misticanza is very young, friendly and excited so she will try to play with you and she's quite big phisically so you have to establish a relation of respect. My cats Tabitha and Gigia are pretty calm, but they're used to jump on the table and to drink from the sink. Lot of fur around :-) but I try to clean as much as possibile. So come only if you love animals and if you are used to them, or you will be unconfortable, and the animals and me too. I don't accept children: read before why.
transit: With ten minutes walk you can reach the underground. Even closer there are buses that go to the archelogical and renaissemental center and to the main railways station. At 1.7 km there are city railway lines that go to Fiumicino Airport, to the beach, to Ostia Antica, to lake Bracciano, to Cerveteri's necropoli.
access: Your room will be completely yours, and you have to remember to lock it or my dog will enter and she will eat your stuff or lick you on the face in the morning :-) But during the day I could need to access the room. The bathroom is shared with me, bring your own soap if you don't want to use mine. :-) I will give you towels. Don't take too long showers and don't spend too much time in the bathroom, it's shared! For 5 euros extra you will be able to wash your clothes with a biodegrable soap ;-) You could leave small stuff in the fridge but please only things that have a vegetable origin, my fridge is vegan! :-) You cannot use the kitchen for cooking for insurance reason. Breakfast is not included. There is unlimited wi-fi access to the internet in the house! There is a TV but it's only to watch DVD, I don't like on-air tv! Check-in is after 4 p.m., check out is before 12 a.m., please respect these times. Normally I cannot change these times because I have guests before you and after you
interaction: I would like to interact a lot with you if I have time, I will be glad! I will be happy to hear your stories, to give you turistic suggestions, to do something togheter if you'll like, to share a bit of live ;-) I am very open minded and I always lived in Rome so I'm quite experienced! I am a warm and nice guy. But sometimes I can be busy so don't get offended if happens that I could not interact a lot with you.
house_rules: Don't break anything if you can! Don't bring animal food. Always close the door of your room.  Be patient with the animals. Check-in is after 4 p.m., check out is before 12 a.m.  Don't be too noisy for the neighbours. Don't spend hours in the shared bathroom. Try to have fun! :-D
host_about:
My name is Alfredo, I was born in Rome and I always lived here. 
I'm a normal guy that doesn't accept to be normal, so very soon I make a mess in my life. 
I am open minded and very curios, I can be very shy and people say that I look very gentle and peaceful. 
I try to always see things from another point of view, but I can be also very lazy in doing real stuff. 
I have a lot of interests but I am also dispersive. 
I can be very simple and very complicated: I have lot of contradictions and doubts! :-)
I am antifascist, antiraxist, antisexist and antispecist. 
I think everyone must be free and alive so I don't eat animal and I don't eat or use anything that comes from animals: someone would say I am vegan. :-) 
I like to read, photography, to spend time on computers, to cook, to eat, to drink, to meet strange people, to love, to relax on the beach, to trekking on mountains, animals, to walk. 

******************
Mi chiamo Alfredo, sono nato a Roma e sempre vissuto qui.
Sono un ragazzo normale a cui non piace la normalità, quindi spesso faccio un casino nella vita.
Sono di mentalità aperta e molto curioso, posso essere molto timido e dicono che sembro molto gentile e pacioso.
Cerco sempre di vedere le cose da un altro punto di vista, ma posso anche essere molto pigro nell'attivarmi.
Ho molti interessi ma sono anche dispersivo.
Posso essere molto semplice e molto complicato: ho un sacco di contraddizioni e dubbi! :-)
Sono antifascista, antirazzista, antisessista e antispecista.
Penso che tutti debbano essere liberi e vivi quindi non mangio animali e non mangio o uso niente che viene dagli animali: qualcuno potrebbe dire che sono vegano. :-)
Mi piace leggere, la fotografia, perdere tempo al pc, cucinare, mangiare, bere, incontrare persone strane, amare, rilassarmi sulla spiaggia, fare trekking in montagna, gli animali, viaggiare.

name: RV 1 Santa Cruz Mtns Bonny Doon
summary: Guests will be sleeping in the RV - which is located in a beautiful gated property, surrounded by giant redwoods trees in Bonny Doon.   20 minutes from downtown Santa Cruz. I live on the property in the main house.  The RV has a small bathroom with a shower and one twin bed.  There is also a second outdoor bathroom with a sink and a toilet located near the RV, as well as an additional outdoor bathroom which contains only a shower.
space: My children and I live in the main house. Current Airbnb guests will be renting one of the two RV's on my property. Each RV has its own listing.  This will be a rustic camping like experience with some modern conveniences...such as outdoor shower with hot and cold water, and additional outdoor bathroom with toilet and sink, a small RV bathroom and a mini RV kitchen with a small refrigerator, microwave, stove. This RV has one twin bed only.

summary: Room 5: 4 people. 1 double bed and 2 single beds.  With breakfast. Minimum 2 nights.
description: Room 5: 4 people. 1 double bed and 2 single beds.  With breakfast. Minimum 2 nights.
host_about:
In the heart of Ealing, known as Queen of suburbs, The Caspian offers cosy rooms with continental breakfast in a friendly family environment. We have been serving the local and international community for decades and the hospitality of The Caspian has not diminished over these years.


Caspian is conveniently nestled on the corner of Haven Green. Set in a Victorian Era house, all rooms are double glazed with TV, free WIFI and seating area provided. Some rooms have period features and large windows with garden view.

We offer a large variety of rooms: diversified by their size, colour and price.

We have onsite parking and a meeting room is available for hire. It offers a pleasant ambiance for board meetings or private reunions.





The Caspian is a 2 minutes’ walk from Ealing Broadway Station and 15 minutes from Central London. Ealing Broadway shopping centres, restaurants and all amenities are a short walk. Our sister La Baguette coffee shop/restaurant offers delicious Tunisian and international food (10% discount for Hotel guests). 

So much is going on in Ealing: Ealing Summer Festivals (Jazz, Blues, Comedy, Beer, Carnival) in July, Ealing Half Marathon in September.
 ...and around Ealing: Sport and Music events at Wembley Stadium all year, and the unique grand Westfield Shopping Malls is a short bus or train ride. The significant Walpole Park along with Pitzhanger Manor are a short stroll from Caspian.

Caspian Hotel is just 20 minutes’ drive from Heathrow Airport. The M4, M40 and A406 motorways are only 5 minutes’ drive.





The Caspian has been visited by top consultant Alex Polizzi from The Hotel Inspector TV Series on 3 consecutive years.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment has a view over green and beautiful Frederiksberg Gardens which is within 5 minutes walking distance, and ideal for runs, walks and picnics. We will leave you a map of the gardens with our favourite spots marked. For instance you can watch the elephants in the neighbouring Copenhagen Zoo. Cafés, bars and restaurants: If you like sunny cafes, there are plenty in our street, in fact almost every building has a different style of café, restaurant or ice cream bar, including our building which has both. All close around 10 pm at the latest, so you will not be disturbed by noise at night. Around the corner is the historical Pile Alle with an abundance of new and really old garden bars and restaurants dating back to the 17th Century, all in the atmosphere of the oldest Frederiksberg village.  Shopping in the area: If you’re into Danish design, almost opposite our building are the outlet shops of world famous Royal Copenhagen (china) and Georg Jensen (jewellery and watches). Our
transit: Bus and metro are within 5 minutes of walking distance. The bus goes straight to the entrance of Tivoli, the City centre of Copenhagen and Strøget in less than 10 minutes. The metro is three short stops from the city and the most popular and famous market of Copenhagen, Torvehallerne. One more metro stop takes you to Nyhavn, the Royal Theatre and the part of Strøget (Copenhagen's No. 1 walking street) with the most exclusive shops.

CURRENT MISSION
Startup. Travel. Enjoying Life. 2017.

ABOUT ME
Hey guys,
just a short introduction to me: 
Currently living in Vienna again - but mostly busy traveling the world while connecting entrepreneurial minds from the globe. I'm supporting and working with the most promising startups in Europe and I'm especially well connected within this scene here in Vienna. 

After finishing my studies in Vienna in 2012 I travelled the US for over 3 months, which was an amazing time for me!

I've already lived in Switzerland, Italy, Germany, Israel and Bangkok - travelled around in Europe, Asia and the US.

I'm an openminded person and I love to meet new people from all over the world with different stories and adventures. 
Vienna is my favorite city, I'm living here for 8 years now and I know all the interesting and most beautiful places to relax, to eat out and to party!

host_about:
Celebrate with family, friends, strangers, with lots of food, cheer and music. Most adventures are a good idea.

Bringing people and ideas together for common good. Challenging journeys, and mischievous plans

Grew up with 3 sisters, loving parents, cats and dogs in the privileged suburbs- see the family weekly, for dinner, or some other excuse

Have a flatmate- PATRICIO, who's from Spain, but grew up in some disproportionate combination of Brazil, Romania, Italy. He's as story-book as you'd imagine, writes comedy, non stop, asks way to many questions and is a good friend. Find him here: on couch surf, Patrick Gornic

I work a lot. I'm good at what I do. I enjoy it It often includes travel (8 countries in the last 12 months) I've autonomy, creative freedom, ADD and an insatiable thirst for more

PHILOSOPHY

Your life to live with whatever limits you wish

Anything is possible if you want it badly enough.

Little is more satisfying than accomplishing what others said you couldnt.

Well done is better than well said, -Ben Franklin

Business is for fun, money is just a bonus.

Why I'm on Couchsurfing

HOW I PARTICIPATE IN COUCHSURFING

Happy to help in the pursuit of seeing the world. It's the people I;ve met that have made my travels possible, I'm just glad to give back.

I have a comfy black leather couch and in the living room which sits across from a BIG flat screen TV (which mostly plays sports) and a hookah. The apartment isn't large, but it is primely located in southern midtown manhattan, between Chelsea and the Flatiron district.

I'd be happy to recommend bars, restaurants, shopping, events, transportation etc. Happy to take yous out and show you how we do in NYC

COUCHSURFING EXPERIENCE

(website hidden)

My roommate, when I was living in Rome, Lucinda, was a member of coach surfing, which was the first time I was exposed to it.

It was great which is why I signed up. Our guest were mostly very polite, offering a bottle of wine, or paying for dinner. Sometimes they only had their company to contribute, which was plenty. We were happy to share our good fortune with others and contribute to the travel community. We were working pubcrawls in Rome at the time, which was mostly an expat community, and had a lot of freedom to work when we pleased, because it was all commission- which allowed us to be flexible with our guests.

I've hearrd stories of it not working out. but from my personal experiences, i havent any regrets.

Interests

(website hidden)

Probably the same as most this couch surf community. Travel, wine, books, music, food, adventure, people, parties, the celebration of creativity.

It's not easy to see the world, this is my chance to give back and help a bit, as so many have already done for me.

Music, Movies & Books

Music: Rock, Rap, World, Jazz, pop

Real hip-hop. BIG, Pac, JayZ, Nas, Joe Budden, and modern day, real rappers. eminem before 8 mile. big pun

classic Rock- 90's/ modern. Led Zep, Pink Floyd, Rolling Stones Hendrix, Bob Dilon. etc pearl jam, red hot chili peppers, nirvana, kings of leon, Queens of the Stone Age

Books: something with adventure, and will teach me something, and well written with descriptive verbs that makes me envisions being a part of the story- embracing the characters emotions and almost confusing which emotions are real and which are just the story im reading

i recommend SHANTARAM, THE SICILIAN, God's Middle Finger, El Narco, the prince, a sunburned country, dante's inferno, istanbul passage.... but i probably most enjoyed these because I was visiting their settings.

One Amazing Thing I've Done

theres been many moments of amazement, stupidity and excitement. Maybe over drinks.

Teach, Learn, Share

You can learn something from everyone if you take the time

Infinitely curious about cultures- Teach me about your traditions, food, holidays, religion, history, superstitions, i wanna know it all, but really i want you to involve me.

I can share with you about the music & media industry in NYC, journalism, modern marketing, the liquor and travel industry who the big players are, especially in tourism and liquor

teach me to cook new food!

Countries I've Visited:

Australia, Austria, Bahamas, Belgium, Brazil, Canada, Cayman Islands, Colombia, Costa Rica, Dominican Republic, Germany, Greece, Guatemala, India, Italy, Monaco, Netherlands, Nicaragua, Oman, Panama, Portugal, Puerto Rico, Spain, Switzerland, Taiwan, Tunisia, Turkey, Ukraine, United Arab Emirates

Countries I've Lived In:    Italy, United States

neighborhood_overview: As described the location is perfect to visit the Vatican Museums and St. Peter's Basilica. You can take a nice walk during the day and also in the evening being a very quiet neighborhood. In 10 minutes you can reach the metro Cipro, through the steps that connect us to the main street with all the services, where you can find restaurants, cafes, shops and all that might be needed for your stay.
notes: The City Tax is not included in the price of  the apartment and is equal to 3.50€ / night per person (for children under 10 years is free). It will be collected in cash upon arrival. We check-in 24h-24h to facilitate business travelers or for those who have their own flight arrival times at night. For this reason, check-in after 20pm hours are charged with a small fee, please check this at time of booking.
transit: The area is well served by public transports, and buses that lead directly in the historic center pass right in front of the house on Viale Vaticano! If you do not like walking to get to the Metro we recommend buying the Rome Pass which includes all public transports, instead of the daily Metro ticket, so you can use all transports, including buses. To reach St. Peter's Basilica it is a 10 minute walk; simply walk along the Vatican Walls and you are there! To reach the Spanish Steps you can take the Metro A (red line) for 4 stops from Cipro, getting off at Piazza di Spagna station. Alternatively, the bus 49 passing on Viale Vaticano, therefore near the easier entrance of the flat, takes you in 10 minutes to Piazza Cavour; from there you can reach the Historical Center of Rome in 5 minutes walk, crossing Ponte Cavour (Via Tomacelli, Via del Corso, Via Condotti and Piazza di Spagna). To reach the Colosseum, always taking the Metro from Cipro (red line) you first arrive at Termini and cha
access: The House will be completely at your disposal.
interaction: We will always be available and at complete disposal to give you all the help and assistance during the stay. We will welcome you at home by providing all the information on the best places to visit in Rome, as well as local cafes, restaurants and Roman trattorias, ice cream and pastry shops, as well public utilities stores such as supermarkets, pharmacies and household items!

host_about:
In the heart of Ealing, known as Queen of suburbs, The Caspian offers cosy rooms with continental breakfast in a friendly family environment. We have been serving the local and international community for decades and the hospitality of The Caspian has not diminished over these years.


Caspian is conveniently nestled on the corner of Haven Green. Set in a Victorian Era house, all rooms are double glazed with TV, free WIFI and seating area provided. Some rooms have period features and large windows with garden view.

We offer a large variety of rooms: diversified by their size, colour and price.

We have onsite parking and a meeting room is available for hire. It offers a pleasant ambiance for board meetings or private reunions.





The Caspian is a 2 minutes’ walk from Ealing Broadway Station and 15 minutes from Central London. Ealing Broadway shopping centres, restaurants and all amenities are a short walk. Our sister La Baguette coffee shop/restaurant offers delicious Tunisian and international food (10% discount for Hotel guests). 

So much is going on in Ealing: Ealing Summer Festivals (Jazz, Blues, Comedy, Beer, Carnival) in July, Ealing Half Marathon in September.
 ...and around Ealing: Sport and Music events at Wembley Stadium all year, and the unique grand Westfield Shopping Malls is a short bus or train ride. The significant Walpole Park along with Pitzhanger Manor are a short stroll from Caspian.

Caspian Hotel is just 20 minutes’ drive from Heathrow Airport. The M4, M40 and A406 motorways are only 5 minutes’ drive.





The Caspian has been visited by top consultant Alex Polizzi from The Hotel Inspector TV Series on 3 consecutive years.
