host_about:
Hello, I'm a friendly Italian man with a very positive outlook on life. 
I am an endlessly curious. I love to experience the world with eyes wide open. I never stop exploring, discovering and evolving.
I love the Arts and creative people! Life to me is a storybook full of fascinating tales. I amass information 'on the hoof' and very little passes me by. Understanding what makes others tick is meat and drink to me and proves to be a source of endless joy.
I always keep my mind active. I love beauty in all forms, I am well educated and I like to remain totally classless. This makes it easy for me to get on with just about any sort of person. I am thought-provoking and even quite deep on occasions.
I organise luxury tours in Italy for small parties and occasionally I escort them, as I am a professional tour guide too. I get involved in other exciting things which keep me busy too, such as painting, reading books, newspaper and cultural magazines, photography, video editing, cycling, theatre, music, fitness and movies.
I strongly believe a very clean, secure, welcoming feel, and comfortable house is of paramount importance for travellers who don't want to break their bank account! 
I have been travelling on my own since the age of 14! I have been an exchange student in Baltimore for a year at the age of 18  and then at 20 I visited 36 States in the U.S. on a three cross Country tour. Been in Hawaii, Canada, Singapore and Malaysia, Maldives, Brazil,  Mexico, Costa Rica, Morocco, Tunisia, Cape Verde, Turkey and all Western European Countries.
When you stay at my place I will make you feel a member of my family as my life's golden rule is to treat others as you wish to be treated! 
I am always on an adventure. Enjoy hearing about people's travels and life styles. It stands to good reason why you would enjoy staying in my home: it is a warm and caring place. 
I look forward to meeting you and show the true Mediterranean hospitality with an English twist!
Sincerely,
Adriano :-)

Socializzo con facilità, rido di gusto, mi intrigano i cervelli acuti e mi innervosicono gli arroganti prepotenti; mi annoiano i "lagnosi" fine a se stessi ma ascolto volentieri chi ha bisogno di un consiglio o di un sostegno per trovare una soluzione. Non sopporto le ingiustizie, la superficialità e mi innamoro di chi è capace di godere delle piccole cose e di chi, come dice Aristotele, "prova un senso di dubbio e di meraviglia, riconosce di non sapere e per liberarsi dall'ignoranza ricerca il conoscere..."

neighborhood_overview: Belleville est un quartier métissé, en pleine transformation. Auparavant très populaire, c'est maintenant le nouveau repère des bobos parisiens pour y vivre une vie de bohème. Venez découvrir la rue des graffeurs, ainsi que les petits bars plein de charme, et les restaurants aux saveurs chinoises, tunisiennes, ou encore franchouillardes. Belleville, c'est aussi l'emplacement idéal pour se balader, au Parc de Belleville (où vous profiterez d'une superbe vue) et aux Buttes Chaumont. Quoi de mieux pour un pique-nique ou un footing matinal ?! Vous trouverez également une super boulangerie près de l'appartement, on vous donnera l'adresse, c'est promis !
transit: Le métro de Belleville se situe à cinq minutes de l'appartement, ainsi que le métro Pyrénées. Des arrêts de bus se situent également à proximité, ainsi qu'une borne vélib dans la rue voisine de celle de l'appartement.

neighborhood_overview: Bushwick is a unique, and colorful neighborhood.  Recently, it was named as the 7th coolest neighborhood in the world, whatever that means! Bushwick is north Brooklyn, on the border of Ridgewood, Queens.  North Brooklyn has a very different feel than Manhattan, but is only a 15 min subway ride to the heart of downtown - Union Square or lower east side.  Recently, there has been a great migration of artists and young working people who have moved out here.   Bushwick has a certain edginess and grit that can be seen with the many murals, art, and graffiti on buildings.   It still has a Hispanic / Caribbean feel and sound, but it has changed dramatically to become more of a melting pot.   Bushwick is soon becoming one of the most coveted neighborhoods in NYC to live in, and rents are going up.  The nightlife is booming, and new restaurants / bars are opening every week.   We have found it contains some of the best and cheapest food in NYC, and in most occasions, choose to eat out here, ra
notes: We love hosting international travelers, as we have both lived and visited abroad.  We have had visitors from Australia, Germany, Italy, Tunisa, France, England, Austria, Sweden, Spain, Mexico, Venezuela, Canada, China, Norway, and of course all over the U.S!!
transit: Very easy 15 mins subway ride to Union Sq on the L.  Williamsburg is only 10 mins subway ride to the Bedford or Lorimer stop.  A second option is to take the M train from Knickerbocker station which gets you to the lower east side in 20 mins.  Both M and L trains are 5 mins walking from the apt.  There is also a bus that runs into downtown Brooklyn on Dekalb Ave.
access: WiFi access, full kitchen, clean bathroom, and a very comfortable living room to sit and relax.
interaction: We are in and out of the apartment.   We both work in Manhattan most days of the week, Bobby works from home 1 or 2 days per week.  We are home in the evenings and love to cook and relax! We both speak Spanish as well.  We tend to give the guests plenty of privacy, but do not mind chatting or having a glass of wine together. We would love to tell you about a fun day or weekend in the city to help you plan your visit!
house_rules: We expect our guests to be reasonable with noise in the late evening and nights. Please no smoking.  Pets are ok. Check in/out might be flexible depending on our schedules. Ask us any questions!
host_location: New York, New York, United States
host_about:
We are a fun, young couple!  Bobby and Alondra reside here in the 2 bedroom apartment.  We have lived in New York for 6+ years, and have decided Bushwick is the best place for us!  Here is a little more about us, our apartment, Bushwick, and everything in between:

We love cooking and eating, are social, and love travelling.  We take lots of weekend trips to visit family and friends.  Alondra is a fantastic cook, loves all things fashion, and is a native Puerto Rican.  Bobby loves his sports, his beer, and originally hails from the great nation of Texas.  We have been hosts since summer of 2014, and we have hosted people from over 35 different cities all over the world!!  We like to socialize with our guests some at nights, but respect privacy always.  We cook 3-4 times a week at home in the evening, and we love to share some wine or beer with our guests!

Our schedules are quite busy, Bobby working in downtown Manhattan at American Express, and Alondra works for Tommy Hilfiger in Chelsea, on the west side of Manhattan.  We both are out during days, but are reachable always and return in the evenings.

Our apartment is beautiful.  The moment we walked in 3 years ago, we both knew it would be our home for sometime to come.  Railroad style, there are 2 big bedrooms on opposite side of the apartment from one another.  The kitchen, bathroom, and living room all have brand new appliances, with high ceilings and recessed lighting.  The brick makes it feel more homey.  The apartment is safe, and the building is quiet.

Bushwick is an awesome place to live.  It has a certain uniqueness to it, the culture, art, and lifestyle are really one of a kind; which make it the most diverse neighborhood in NYC.  We have also found it contains some of the best and cheapest food also.  With easy access to Union Sq and the lower east side (each 15 mins) it's super accessible to Manhattan so you never feel too far away from the center of the world.  We can't imagine living anywhere else in NYC.

Of course we know New York very well, so we are more than willing to give advice, and help plan out a fun day or weekend.  We are looking forward to being your host!!

host_about:
Hello, I am  Petya Hottz. 
Welcome to my great international family in New York. Let me show you around.
I live in a 3 bedroom apartment in Astoria, Queens, with my husband Thiago, who is from Brazil and a Chinese boy Jack. I have a lot of great locations and  of course they are not in the same apartment. Most are in Astoria around us, Woodside, Jackson Heights and  MANHATTAN.  All locations are very nice, clean, well experienced hosting people from all around the world, in pretty convenient and safe  neighborhoods. You are very welcome to be part of my little, international family. 
 I am originally from Bulgaria and I speak English, Bulgarian, Russian, and a little bit of French. I am a very friendly positive person and I am also very open to foreign cultures, music, food, and customs. New York is a very unique city because people are from all around the world and contribute to the diversity of daily living.
As a professional figure skater I have participated in competitions throughout most of Europe. As a child I traveled often with my family to France, Germany, Italy, California, Tunisia and Spain. In addition, I have traveled extensively to North America, Brazil. I love to engage in sports, yoga, tennis, skating, skiing, swimming, hiking, music, dancing and I love to cook. My father and my brother in law are professional chefs. I guess I inherited the passion from them to prepare delicious foods. I would love for you to experience my cuisine.
In addition about my rooms, they all are located in a great neighborhood with restaurants, bars, international food, stores, libraries, parks, schools, shopping malls, and cinemas. Everything is nearby and convenient to public transportation which runs 24 hours a days. It is only 5-25 min to NYC. Or if you need a taxi, they are abundantly available outside the (URL HIDDEN) location is located a block or a few blocks from  subway stations. All rooms are new furnished, AC, WiFi and Cable, all included in the price. I also can offer you occasional free skating classes with me at the local rink.
Welcome to my apartment. I know you are going to feel like you are home. I am waiting for you my new friend. Welcome to New York!

The bi-weekly market has some of the best produce you will find in Paris. The shops on rue des Pyrénées include some of the best cheese store, butchers and boulangeries.   Restaurants include classic brasseries, such as the amazing Bistro Chantefable (across the street)  as well as the trendier restaurants that have opened in the past few years.   A great neighborhood to discover, but also minutes away, by metro, from all of Paris' main sights.

host_about:
Ce qui me manquerait le plus serait de renoncer au voyage qui me donne l'assurance, d'être surprise chaque jour par les rencontres et les journées imprévisibles
Le continent le plus surprenant, pour moi, est l'Afrique (Casamance au Senegal)
où j'ai construit une maison avec les habitants du village. Il s'agit d'un véritable artisanat de la construction, confection de la brique elle-même, ceci sans beaucoup d'outillage
Le Vénézuela et la Colombie m'ont enchantée par leur vitalité
Le Moyen Orient (Syrie Jordanie Liban) m'a séduite également car j'ai en la chance de les parcourir avant ces événements sanglants
Maroc, Algérie, Tunisie si proche de nous donne à réfléchir
La lecture, Le Cinéma pr toutes les histoires racontées
Trouver le temps de ne rien faire et se dire à la fin de la journée "je n'ai rien fait"
donne une satisfaction à la paresseuse qui se cache dans l'hyperactive que je suis

description: An independent guest studio on the second floor (G+1), perfect for up to two guests and a child. Comes with english-speaking family living downstairs to make you feel at home during your stay in the lively quarter of la Folie-Méricourt. A guest studio on the second floor (G+1) in the lively 11th arrondissement, between Canal St Martin and Menilmontant/Belleville. One large thirty Sqm (323 ft2) room, with en-suite bathroom, freshly renovated, will comfortably accommodate one or two guests - baby optional but welcome. The studio includes a bathroom (with walk-in shower), a mini kitchen including a mix-mode oven, toaster, kettle, coffee machine (but no cooking plates), fridge and freezer.  Internet access provided via WiFi (fiber).   We can provide a baby crib and bathtub on request (€ 20 fee). The neighbourhood offers a wide array of restaurants, stores and take-away stalls, and two laundromats within a 100 meters on the same street. We will welcome you on arrival and see you out on depa
neighborhood_overview: The Folie-Méricourt quarter brings together a wide variety of people : it has its share of hipsters, thanks of the many  bars and trendy eateries, but is also home to many working-class families, professionals and boutique businesses. The village-like neighbourhood also seems to make a point of disproving clichés, with people of many ethnicities and creeds living together amicably, which, as a visitor, means you'll have no problems eating out and shopping for groceries to your taste ! Go for a coffee or a show at La Maison des Metallos (the old metalworkers union house turned theater), or check the farmers market on Richard Lenoir to find typical french foodstuffs (including creole and Tunisian delicacies).  Walk up the street to visit Menilmontant and its north-african eateries, then head through Belleville's chinatown to see Paris from the terrace above the park on Belleville hill, or go west and stroll along Canal St Martin : every other street brings a different mood.
notes: The neighbourhood is lively and can get a bit loud on weekend nights : since the studio's windows face street-side, and despite good soundproofing glass, we do not recommend it if you are a light sleeper. We have iron and board downstairs for you to borrow, and same goes for phone landline (calls to many international LL are no-charge, too). Minimum 2 nights Stay. Paris survival tip  :  Just make sure to open with "Bonjour" before you break into english (a mildly apologetic look helps, too) and you'll find people get out of their way to be helpful. :)
transit: Moving around with public transportation is easy (as is generally the case inside Paris) :  The République station is a 5' walk, and is a major Metro (tube) hub.  There are several other Metro and bus lines within a few hundred yards  range. [Closest is Parmentier, on line N°3] If you feel adventurous, the Velib service (pick up and ride bicycles) dares you to try biking around Paris !
access: The studio includes a bathroom (with walk-in shower), a mini kitchen including a mix-mode oven, toaster, kettle, coffee machine (but no cooking plates), fridge and freezer.  Internet access provided via WiFi (fiber).   We can provide a baby crib and bathtub on request (€ 20 fee). The neighbourhood offers a wide array of restaurants, stores and take-away stalls, and two laundromats within a 100 meters on the same street.
interaction: We will welcome you on arrival and see you out on departure. You're welcome to reach out at any time during your stay, should you need any help or tips – we live right downstairs We speak fluent French and English, can do horrible things to a number of other languages and will be delighted to help you find your bearings in the neighbourhood and around Paris. If you have any special needs or preferences that can't easily be accommodated in a pinch, please let us know ahead of your visit so we can look into arrangements by the time of your arrival.
house_rules: We go by the "don't be a dick" ruleset. EX: The studio is nominally non-smoking, but if you toast one by the window, we probably won't tell your mom. In the same spirit, we have no objections to pets, but you're accountable for yours : if your purse dog is in the habit of yapping in anguish when left alone, don't lock it in the flat when you go out at night, lest it gets rescued. Please make an enquiry prior to requesting a reservation : I do my best to keep the calendar updated but life is known to happen (guests extending their stay, visiting relatives, etc). Also, we shamelessly discriminate against people who can't be bothered to RTFM. ;) When in doubt, ask : we'll try our best to answer any question.
host_about:
Born in Paris, and currently enjoying the parisian life, I also love to travel with my partner and our 9 years old son, both for leisure and work.

Over the years, we've lived and sojourned in 3 1/2 continents (still have S-Am and Oceania to go), and wherever we go we carry with us the memories and friendships garnered around the world.

Being Frogs, we care more about the journey than the destination... also we'll try to eat almost anything, at least once.

/ 

Native et (ces temps-ci) résidente Parisienne, j’aime aussi voyager en compagnie de mon partenaire et notre fils de 9 ans, aussi bien pour le travail que le plaisir.

Au cours des années, nous avons vécu ou séjourné sur trois à quatre continents (l’Océanie et l’Amérique du Sud restent à venir), et ou que nous soyons, nous emportons avec nous les souvenirs et amitiés collectionnés autour du globe.

Etant français, le voyage nous importe plus que la destination, et nous sommes prêts à toutes les aventures culinaires !

host_location: New York, New York, United States
host_about:
Hi there! I am a young Canadian opera singer, and I am always keen on meeting interesting people from everywhere on this globe.

I travel a lot for work, so I am generally looking for a places where I can recollect myself within all this travels. A place to call home for a few days (or even a few hours!). I am a non-smoker, respectful and decent woman who is looking for peaceful, calm and quiet places with likewise minds and values. 

I also speak Français, Arabic, ein bisschen Deutsch, e po d'italiano! 
I am sure we can find a way to communicate!

5 things I can't live without?

1- My suitcase

2- My computer (And I will add in this same category my smart phone and my iPad)

3- Music (and my earphones, obvi)

4- Exercise (I'm on the road constantly, so I run - or try to... - as my exercise of choice as I can only pack my light vibrams 5 fingers shoes, and a few light pieces of gear, and I'm set! It's also a great way to discover and visit places when you travel on your own!)

5- My family and friends (no explanation needed here ;)

Favorite destination? Hard to tell. I LOVED Costa Rica, and Bocas del Toro in Panama. Tunisia is also a wonderful country. I also (very randomly) fell in love with Reykjavik, Iceland... ?!

I love cooking, and when on the road, I try to eat as much healthy as one can. But I am a sucker for Thai food... :S

My life motto? "Be good. And if you can't be good, BE GOOD AT IT!"

host_about:
Hello, I am  Petya Hottz. 
Welcome to my great international family in New York. Let me show you around.
I live in a 3 bedroom apartment in Astoria, Queens, with my husband Thiago, who is from Brazil and a Chinese boy Jack. I have a lot of great locations and  of course they are not in the same apartment. Most are in Astoria around us, Woodside, Jackson Heights and  MANHATTAN.  All locations are very nice, clean, well experienced hosting people from all around the world, in pretty convenient and safe  neighborhoods. You are very welcome to be part of my little, international family. 
 I am originally from Bulgaria and I speak English, Bulgarian, Russian, and a little bit of French. I am a very friendly positive person and I am also very open to foreign cultures, music, food, and customs. New York is a very unique city because people are from all around the world and contribute to the diversity of daily living.
As a professional figure skater I have participated in competitions throughout most of Europe. As a child I traveled often with my family to France, Germany, Italy, California, Tunisia and Spain. In addition, I have traveled extensively to North America, Brazil. I love to engage in sports, yoga, tennis, skating, skiing, swimming, hiking, music, dancing and I love to cook. My father and my brother in law are professional chefs. I guess I inherited the passion from them to prepare delicious foods. I would love for you to experience my cuisine.
In addition about my rooms, they all are located in a great neighborhood with restaurants, bars, international food, stores, libraries, parks, schools, shopping malls, and cinemas. Everything is nearby and convenient to public transportation which runs 24 hours a days. It is only 5-25 min to NYC. Or if you need a taxi, they are abundantly available outside the (URL HIDDEN) location is located a block or a few blocks from  subway stations. All rooms are new furnished, AC, WiFi and Cable, all included in the price. I also can offer you occasional free skating classes with me at the local rink.
Welcome to my apartment. I know you are going to feel like you are home. I am waiting for you my new friend. Welcome to New York!

Je suis une Alsacienne qui aime accueillir, faire plaisir et faire découvrir ma belle région. Actuellement entre London et Strasbourg, je vous invite à venir passer un petit ou long séjour dans mon duplex/chambre. Il est cosy, accueillant et proche des commodités pour faciliter votre passage dans notre belle région. Je suis une amoureuse des voyages (London, Afrique du Sud, Croatie, Portugal, Espagne, Tunisie...), j'aime découvrir de nouvelles cultures, de nouveaux paysages et les spécialités culinaires du pays ou villes que je visite. Donc si vous voulez des bons plans restaurants sur Strasbourg ou alentours, je suis de bons conseils ;) Au plaisir de vous rencontrer ou de vous parler...

name: Spacious 1 bedroom apartment in Salamanca
summary: Bright and spacious 1 bedroom apartment in Salamanca, walking distance from 2 main metro stations.  Perfect location for exploring the city as well as for business travellers.  Air conditioning, Heating, Wifi and TV with Netflix. My home is comfortable and cosy.  Mi casa es su casa!
space: Welcome to my spacious yet cosy 1 bedroom apartment in Salamanca.  The apartment is situated near 2 main metro stops and walking distance from supermarkets and shopping area. The apartment is ideal for a couple of days exploring the vibrant city as well as for business travelers looking to relax.

host_about:
I'm originally from Carthage, Tunisia. I've been living in Montreal since 2011. I love travelling and going to cruises. I'm a well organized and clean person. I like TM meditation and I'm a very spiritual person. I speak 4 languages very well and I am learning my fifth one which is Chinese Mandarin ( It is not easy I know ).
I fell in love with Montreal in summer 2010 when I was visiting (I I was living in Toronto that period of time )  and then decided to move in ;) 
I am a dog lover I have a lovely pug with which my life became more interesting I love to know ppl from all over the world and discover new things.
I am a sociable and a helpful person with a great sense of humour.
Airbnb is a great way to to explore new places , to have new experiences and especially to know more interesting people and that is the main reason of my presence in this site so if you are my future guest please do not hesitate to contact me in order to get to know each others :)
My Life motto is the LLL which is  LIVE EVERY MOMENT - LAUGH EVERY DAY - LOVE BEYOND WORDS

Very quiet, confortable, this flat can host up to 4 people (one double bed and a sofa bed). Is available a kitchen with oven, a bathroom with shower, washing machine (to be paid separately). At few metres there are two beautiful parks where to relax!
space: A modern two-rooms flat, recently renovated in a trendy suburb, full of life and not far from the center, well linked with public transport. The double bed is very confortable, the street is quiet. IMPORTANT: the double bed is for 2 people, but in the living room there is a sofa bed to host up to 4 people with only €15 more per night per person.

neighborhood_overview: Pigneto is the area of young people and full of night life! In the morning, in the close pedestrian area there is well-stocked street market and the area looks familiar. In the nights is full of restaurants, pubs, bars where you can enjoy night life. If you don't like night life, no problems: the house is not in the most busy area, but in an adiacent street very quiet where you can relax in peace!
notes: Now we don't have yet internet in the house, but just out of the door there are many place where to use wi-fi for free :-)
transit: At few metres there is the stop of many trams that will lead you to the main train station termini and historical center. The area is  very well linked to the place where you will arrive in Rome! Train station, bus stations, airports.
access: You can use the full equipped kitchen to cook your meals and eat them on the table in the living room. You can relax on the sofa and watch TV (also if I suggest you to enjoy Rome!) The bathroom has a very modern shower and a washing machine (to be paid separately - €5 for washing). I cannot include breakfast in my offer (always because of the italian law) but you can cook your own! Check-in is after 4 p.m., check out is before 12 a.m., please respect these times. Normally I cannot change these times because I have guests before you and after you. For pratical reasons it's not possible to leave your luggage before the check-in or after the check-out. In the not far Termini station there is a depot for luggage. If you want to be sure to be able to do an early check-in or a late check-out simply book another nights before or after your stay! ;-) Of course we will have to agree for the check-in time as soon as possibile and anyway some days BEFORE that you arrive. You can see on the Airbnb
interaction: With pleasure we will meet at the check in, I will give you a free map of Roma, I will show you the house, let you sign a contract  for the staying (necessary for italian law) and ask you for your details because I have to send them to the italian government. In case of problems or needs I will be available to help you. If you would like to interact more, I will be glad to know you better, do something together and maybe make friendship ! :-)
house_rules: Non rompere niente! Chiudi sempre le finestre quando esci. Non aprire la porta di casa ad estranei. Il check-in è dalle 16, il check-out è entro le 12. Non disturbare i vicini, specialmente di notte. Risparmia energia per la Terra. Non perdere le chiavi. Divertiti! :-D ********** Don't break anything! Always close the windows when you exit. Don't open the front door to anyone that you don't know. Check-in is after 4 p.m., check out is before 12 a.m. Don't be too noisy for the neighbours, especially at night. Save energy for the Earth. Don't lose the keys. Try to have fun! :-D
host_about:
My name is Alfredo, I was born in Rome and I always lived here. 
I'm a normal guy that doesn't accept to be normal, so very soon I make a mess in my life. 
I am open minded and very curios, I can be very shy and people say that I look very gentle and peaceful. 
I try to always see things from another point of view, but I can be also very lazy in doing real stuff. 
I have a lot of interests but I am also dispersive. 
I can be very simple and very complicated: I have lot of contradictions and doubts! :-)
I am antifascist, antiraxist, antisexist and antispecist. 
I think everyone must be free and alive so I don't eat animal and I don't eat or use anything that comes from animals: someone would say I am vegan. :-) 
I like to read, photography, to spend time on computers, to cook, to eat, to drink, to meet strange people, to love, to relax on the beach, to trekking on mountains, animals, to walk. 

******************
Mi chiamo Alfredo, sono nato a Roma e sempre vissuto qui.
Sono un ragazzo normale a cui non piace la normalità, quindi spesso faccio un casino nella vita.
Sono di mentalità aperta e molto curioso, posso essere molto timido e dicono che sembro molto gentile e pacioso.
Cerco sempre di vedere le cose da un altro punto di vista, ma posso anche essere molto pigro nell'attivarmi.
Ho molti interessi ma sono anche dispersivo.
Posso essere molto semplice e molto complicato: ho un sacco di contraddizioni e dubbi! :-)
Sono antifascista, antirazzista, antisessista e antispecista.
Penso che tutti debbano essere liberi e vivi quindi non mangio animali e non mangio o uso niente che viene dagli animali: qualcuno potrebbe dire che sono vegano. :-)
Mi piace leggere, la fotografia, perdere tempo al pc, cucinare, mangiare, bere, incontrare persone strane, amare, rilassarmi sulla spiaggia, fare trekking in montagna, gli animali, viaggiare.

name: Lovely vintage flat
summary: Quiet, neat and fully furnished flat, decorated in a vintage style.
space: The apartment is located on the third floor of a typical 1930s building near what we call « the countryside in Paris ». It  is an ideal base to explore the local life.  It can accommodate two guests in a comfortable double bed and 1 extra guest in a sofa bed. It is perfect for couples who want to enjoy romantic days in Paris, solo travellers who want to experience the town as a local, businessmen/women who are tired of staying in hotels, families with one kid and close friends who are looking for a cosy and private place to stay. Decorated in a vintage style, it has everything you need to feel at home. The apartment is accessible by an elevator leading into a quiet and cosy living room with a comfortable sofa-bed (80x200cm). You are in walking distance

host_about:
Bonjour, 

Je suis Clémence, je vis et travaille à Paris et j'adore cette ville. Tellement de choses à faire à découvrir, je ne m'ennuie jamais.

Je suis créatrice de mode et mon appartement est à l'image de mon métier et de ma personnalité: coloré et chaleureux.

 L'été est ma période favorite, de nombreux festivals sont organisés dans la ville et j'aime surtout danser le " Tango argentin " dans la rue, c'est ma passion.
 Si vous visitez Paris l'été vous pouvez aller vous promener le long des quais de seine ( quai saint Bernard ) et admirer les différentes danses ( salsa, tango, rock,... ) peut-être que vous aurez vous aussi envie de vous y mettre car c'est à cette endroit que j'ai commencé à danser.

J'aime également parcourir Paris avec ma bicyclette, découvrir de nouveaux endroits, de nouveaux quartiers, des quartiers insolites et intimes: miam! Un brunch à la Butte aux cailles, bronzer et lire un bon livre aux Parc des Buttes Chaumont, Sortir boire un verre au Café Chérie,44 boulevard de la villette, ou dans le quartier Oberkampf.

Pour les sorties shopping direction le Marais, les friperies et les boutiques de créateurs. Et souvent j'en profite pour manger une glace chez Pozzetto, des glaces italiennes délicieuses, 39 Rue du Roi de Sicile.

De plus, j'adore voyager j'ai visité les Etats-Unis, le Canada, le Maroc, la Tunisie, et quelques pays d'Europe, en général au sud pour le soleil. Je voyage plutôt avec un sac à dos et je loge chez l'habitant ou en auberge de jeunesse. Je commence à apprendre l'espagnol et j'adore ça, j'aimerais aller en Argentine l'année prochaine.

A bientôt,
Clémence.

neighborhood_overview: Ditmars, Astoria is a vibrant neighborhood. One of the nicest place to live in NYC. There are plenty of restaurants and stores walking distance from the studio (2 blocks away) Artichoke pizzeria, Greek restaurants, Japanese, starbucks etc.. The studio is also walking distance from Astoria park which has a free outdoor swimming pool, running tracks, tennis courts, soccer ground, picnic area, free outdoor movies and an amazing view of Manhattan skyline. Ditmars area is a diverse neighborhood. It has both the feel of a bustling commercial area and a residential vibe. You will still have fantastic access to businesses, markets, bakeries, and restaurants. There are some famous restaurants/bakery few minutes walk from the house: Bareburger, Artichoke Pizza, Brooklyn Bagel &Coffee Company, Taverna Kyclades, Martha Country Bakery.
notes: Myself and Anthony love to interact with people. We would be more than happy to give you list of restaurants, bars, list of museums, parks, clubs and broadway shows worth seeing in New York.  We will do everything we can to make your stay comfortable and to make you feel that you are living in a home away from home. I am from France and i speak French, Spanish and English and Anthony speak Nepalese, Hindi and English. Bonjour! Je m'appelle Laura. Je suis française. Mon compagnon et moi habitons à New York dans le quartier de Ditmars Astoria, Queens. Nous sommes situés à seulement 15 min de Manhattan en métro (le métro marche 24h/24). Ditmars est un quartier vivant et multiculturel, plein de restaurants, bars, commerces, laveries.. Si c'est votre première visite à New York, nous serons ravis de partager bons plans et autres activités sympas à faire à New York! Hola! Soy francesa-peruana. Hablo frances y español. Si se sienten mas comodo communicar en español avisanme :)
transit: The studio is 2 blocks away from the N train line which takes you directly to Manhattan: 59th str & Lexington Ave., Central Park and Times Square. host_about:
Two professionals in New York City, myself, originally from France and my fiancee Anthony originally from Nepal. We both love to travel, we love trying different authentic cuisines and we like to learn about different cultures. Me and my Anthony have so far travelled to Netherlands, France, Spain, Belgium, Greece, Germany, Italy, England, Sweden, Czech Republic, Morocco, Tunisia, Peru, Puerto rico, Bahamas, Mexico, Costa Rica, Canada,Dubai, Turkey, Nepal and India.

However for us “In terms of worldwide international cities, New York City is the best.”

My fiancée speaks Nepali fluently and I am French and I speak French, Spanish and English fluently. I have couple of listing New York City and a place in Kathmandu Nepal listed on AIR BNB and on Home Away site.

Anthony's hobby beside traveling includes playing Soccer, Golfing, Surfing, biking, jazz music, watching musicals, broadway shows, visiting art galleries and I enjoy Salsa Dancing, hiking, arts, museums, biking and skiing.

Motto: "Treat others in the same manner as you would like to be treated"

name: Athens noir: 1930s vibe on the East Mediterranean
summary: This 160m penthouse & terrace garden is ideal for sampling Athens' very core. Instant access to museums, entertainment districts, neoclassical architectural walks, shopping & Documenta. You’ll love its belle époque aesthetic, innercity and Lykavitos Hill views, the quiet you'll experience despite the hyper-central location between Exarcheia and Omonoia Sq. When not exploring, chill under the pergola in the huge corner terrace. Ideal for academics, journos, couples, flaneurs, architects, artists.
space: An architect-designed and immaculately-equipped apartment offered by the Hiboux creative architectural collective (URL HIDDEN) and part of a network of centrally-located properties in Athens, Beirut, Istanbul and Tunis, dedicated to reminding us of an earlier, kinder period of cosmopolitan coexistence in the Mediterranean.  Interiors feature 1950s oak-panelled floors, Persian carpets; period Victorian and French gas-lamps, appliques and suspension-lamps; antique wooden furniture from the early 20th century; original paintings and photography. The huge terrace boasts citrus, olive and walnut trees, alongside an architectural masterpiece: an intricate, 1880s Parisian-style pergola, composed of over 500 individual pieces of welded metal. Included in the booking is a unique, illustrated, insider's guide to contemporary Athens.

neighborhood_overview: Tzortz (George) Street is positioned between bustling Kaningos Square, the shops and public transport of Patision Avenue, and the bars, restaurants, bookshops and vinyl stores of Exarheia Square. It is a 5' walk from major tourist destinations such as the National Archaeological Museum, and walking distance from the neoclassical mansions, gardens and terraces of the Benaki and Numismatic Museums and the separate buildings housing the Islamic and Modern Art collections in Kerameikos and Pireos Street respectively. In the neighbourhood, you are a 10' walk away from the Athens Central Market where, early in the morning you can prowl for the freshest fish, meat, vegetable and fruit alongside the chefs of Athens' best restaurants, before spiriting your haul back to the apartment's professionally-equipped kitchen to whip up culinary feasts. There are some 40 cinemas within 2km of the apartment, including historical indoor halls and beautiful open-air venues for the warm summer months.  Some
notes: This is not a made-for-Airbnb apartment! Lovingly-renovated and furnished with one-off items of furniture and decor, it is a much-loved space and - should you be booking it - you are expected to look after it as if it was your own. Please take your shoes off at the door, wear different footwear on the terrace and inside the apartment, refrain from smoking, and desist from hosting any parties.
transit: Your location is so central that you can walk to most attractions. But it's also amazing for mass transportation, via the nearby Omonoia and Akadimias transportation hubs (5' walk from the apartment in either direction). Metro and urban railway in Omonoia, buses in Akadimias.  Omonoia: Hop onto the Metro Red Line (to the Acropolis, Syntagma, airport and the National Museum of Modern Art) or the urban rail's Green Line to the seaport or the northern suburbs. There is also a large number of bus routes that take you all over the city, both its seaside suburbs and the hilly, cooler northern ones. If you want to go by taxi, there's a taxi-rank axis 1' walk from the apartment on Kaningos Square.  Major sights: The National Archaeological Museum is a 5' walk past the Polytechnic, while the new Acropolis Museum is four stops on the metro Red Line in the Hellinikon direction.
access: The entire apartment (100m2) and extensive terrace (60ms) with the exception of a locked storage room
interaction: I will be in touch with you throughout your stay, alongside dedicated housekeeper Meski
house_rules: Please take off your shoes at the entrance. Protect the parquet flooring by not using the same footwear on the terrace as inside the house. Please be mindful of the environment by turning off the heating or a/c when leaving the apartment. And please be considerate to neighbours by having  no loud parties.
host_about: I'm a humanitarian emergency videographer for the UN, working mostly in the East Mediterranean, North Africa and West Asia. I'm fluent in Arabic, Persian, Turkish and Greek, and I have a soft spot for the two pumas in Athens' zoological park.
